\par\par \b \uc2 2024: Placing diplomacy and dialogue front and center\b0\par\par\uc2 814 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 January 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Marty Natalegawa, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The commencement of a new year is a time when projections are commonly made of global and regional conflicts to watch or new ones to anticipate.\par \par \uc2 Certainly, as 2024 begins, conflicts persist. And the costs, in human life and material damages, have been nothing short of catastrophic.\par \par \uc2 Far from subsiding, the conflict in Gaza shows worrying signs of widening to encompass the wider Middle East region. The toll on human life--women and children included--is severely testing our true sense of common humanity.\par \par \uc2 Elsewhere, the conflict in Ukraine continues to adversely affect geopolitical dynamics among nuclear-armed adversaries with the attendant unimaginable potential consequences.\par \par \uc2 The continent of Africa has its fair share of deadly conflicts, often simultaneously local-national-regional in character, which persist as global attention turns elsewhere.\par \par \uc2 Here in the Indo-Pacific, an "arc of instability" and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  continue to loom. Long-existing and simmering territorial disputes--land as well as maritime--have resurfaced, fuelled by competitive geopolitical dynamics.\par \par \uc2 A trust \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  permeates not only among the well-recognized geopolitical rivals the United States and China, but also between other major actors in the region, India and China for instance, and between the countries of Northeast Asia.\par \par \uc2 In Southeast Asia, twin tests of ASEAN's relevance known at the beginning of 2023, namely the tensions and potential for unintended open conflict in the South China Sea and the ever-worsening situation in Myanmar, persist as 2024 begins. The hoped-for progress on these issues during Indonesia's much-anticipated chairmanship of ASEAN, remained precisely that, mere hope.\par \par \uc2 The regional architecture, long considered inclusive with ASEAN bringing countries of the Indo-Pacific under a common tent despite their varying interests and perspectives, is fraying under the weight of intensified geopolitical competition.\par \par \uc2 Alarming still, the much-needed spirit of cooperative partnership needed to address global commons issues such as climate change, \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  health, the management of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and fast-changing technology, including artificial intelligence (AI), has been desperately scant.\par \par \uc2 Instead, global issues have been increasingly weaponized, infused with competitive and divisive geopolitical dynamics. Domestic political dynamics-- including electoral politics--further complicate matters as foreign policies become increasingly approached through a narrow domestic lens and are increasingly transactional.\par \par \uc2 Such well-defined conflicts and tensions that have weighed on 2023--barring some unexpected transformation--will likely continue in 2024. And of course, there are bound to be the "unknowns".\par \par \uc2 For instance, at the beginning of the years concerned, few would have anticipated the COVID-19 pandemic or the conflicts in Ukraine and Gaza. Beyond the known contours of existing conflicts and tensions, short of having a crystal ball, we simply do not know what lies in store.\par \par \uc2 However, such somber anticipation need not induce passivism or a sense of defeatism. Far from it. Such challenges, and lest it be forgotten, opportunities, ahead remind us of the need for a surge in diplomacy and dialogue.\par \par \uc2 Founded on this belief in the efficacy of dialogue and diplomacy, late last year I had the opportunity to convene the first meeting of the Amity Circle. The group brings together individuals with extensive \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  experience in the fields of diplomacy, foreign \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , international relations and related subjects.\par \par \uc2 The Amity Circle's core tenet is the belief in the value of diplomacy and dialogue as means to manage and resolve present and future challenges and, significantly, to find opportunities sustainably and equitably for the benefit of the global community.\par \par \uc2 Its members are motivated by the conviction that diplomacy, dialogue, negotiation, mediation and action-oriented analysis, as well as informed counsel, offer the potential for positive management of various complex dynamics of our time.\par \par \uc2 These dynamics include: first, the convergence between national-regional-global level issues and second, the projection and impact of geopolitical dynamics on other issues such as commerce, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the environment, energy security, food security, pandemics, technology and social development goals.\par \par \uc2 It seeks to promote an understanding of some of the key drivers of change in East Asia, the Indo-Pacific and beyond. The members recognize ASEAN's important past contributions and yet also the urgent need to ensure its continued relevance.\par \par \uc2 The Amity Circle assembles individuals, with broad and deep experience both in bilateral as well as multilateral diplomacy, who share a strong belief that the present multifaceted and multilayered challenges and opportunities demand comprehensive and common approaches by stakeholders.\par \par \uc2 They share the conviction that all stakeholders--governments, international organizations, businesses and civil society --have important stakes in promoting diplomacy and dialogue as modalities to address common challenges.\par \par \uc2 They share a common concern about the recent headwinds against diplomacy, dialogue and multilateralism.\par \par \uc2 As 2024 commences, diplomacy and dialogue must be placed front and center in dealing with what the year offers.\par \par \uc2 _____________________\par \par \uc2 A former foreign minister of Indonesia and the convenor of the Amity Circle\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240114ek1e00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
