\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIAN  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2  CONTINUING TO SHOW STRONG RESILIENCE: INDRAWATI\b0\par\par\uc2 396 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 January 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Cindy Frishanti Octavia\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - The Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is continuing to show resilient performance amidst global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown, according to Minister of Finance, Sri \uc2 Mulyani Indrawati\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "In the midst of global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and slowdown, the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains resilient, supported by strong domestic demand," Indrawati said at a Financial System Stability Committee (KSSK) press conference in Jakarta on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Up till the third quarter of 2023, the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  recorded a growth of 5.05 percent (year to date), mainly supported by consumption and investment.\par \par \uc2 The minister highlighted that consumption activity is still strong, supported by controlled inflation and a declining unemployment rate, with the state revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (APBN) serving as shock absorbers and helping maintain people"s purchasing power.\par \par \uc2 Investment has also shown a strengthening trend since the first quarter of 2023. Strengthening investment is in line with the accelerated implementation of National Strategic Projects (PSN).\par \par \uc2 Entering the fourth quarter of 2023, Indrawati continued, signs of resilience in domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity continued, which were reflected in the consistently expansive manufacturing \uc2 PMI\uc2  (purchasing managers" index) figures and continued trade balance surplus.\par \par \uc2 There were also several early indicators that were still strong, such as the real sales index and consumer confidence.\par \par \uc2 Given those developments, Indrawati projected \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of around 5.0 percent for 2023, a decline in the unemployment rate to 5.32 percent, and the poverty rate to 9.36 percent.\par \par \uc2 The minister said she is optimistic that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will reach 5.2 percent in 2024.\par \par \uc2 The optimism stems from the general elections, which usually have a positive impact on consumption activities, both in terms of government and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  consumption.\par \par \uc2 The government is also confident that investment performance will continue to be strong, considering the progress of PSNs, which are in the completion stage.\par \par \uc2 During the press conference on Tuesday, Indrawati said that the KSSK continues to be committed to strengthening coordination and synergy for maintaining the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 This is being done by increasing awareness about the risk of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  this year, with the \uc2 World Bank\uc2  estimating that the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will slide from 3 percent in 2022 to 2.5 percent in 2023 and weaken further to 2.4 percent in 2024.\par \par \uc2 (T.C009/A/A063/A063) 30-01-2024 17:40:09\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240130ek1u000ul\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
