\par\par \b \uc2 Used cars, motorbikes buoy auto market\b0\par\par\uc2 Aditya Hadi, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 926 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 January 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Analysts expect new car sales in Indonesia to bounce back this year from the 2023 slump. The market share of electric vehicles (EVs) remains small but is growing fast.\par \par \uc2 As reported earlier this month, nationwide new car sales plummeted 4 percent to 1 million vehicles last year, down from 1.05 million units sold in 2022, based on data from the Association of Indonesian Automotive Manufacturers (Gaikindo).\par \par \uc2 However, new motorcycle sales continued their uptrend, surging by 20 percent to 6.24 million units from 5.22 million sold the previous year, according to the Indonesian Motorcycle Industry Association (AISI). That number is expected to grow to 6.5 million units this year, exceeding pre-pandemic levels.\par \par \uc2 Loan disbursement for used car purchases has also been growing.\par \par \uc2 Analysts argue there may be a shift in \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  from new cars to cheaper alternatives, such as used cars and two-wheelers. However, the experts also projected new car sales to bounce back this year, along with the rise of increasingly popular EVs.\par \par \uc2 Gaikindo attributed the drop in new car sales mainly to slower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in last year's second half and noted that a hawkish monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  had encouraged local lenders to tighten loan disbursement.\par \par \uc2 "As a result, vehicle sales declined, because 80 percent of new vehicle purchases are done through loans from financial institutions," Gaikindo's general secretary Kukuh Kumara said on Jan. 16, as quoted by CNBC Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Koketso Tsoai, an automotive industry analyst with research firm \uc2 Fitch Solutions\uc2 , agreed that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's decision to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  had contributed to a slowdown in demand for new vehicles last year but believed it was not the only factor.\par \par \uc2 "We also contend that the reimplementation of the luxury sales \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on vehicles has had a detrimental effect on car sales. During the pandemic, the suspension of this \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  was a critical measure that supported the automotive industry by boosting consumer demand," Tsoai told The Jakarta Post on Monday.\par \par \uc2 Rising fuel prices have also burdened consumers' capacity to afford new vehicles, while political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding the upcoming general elections may have made potential buyers more cautious, he added.\par \par \uc2 Tsoai also noted that the country's automotive market had recorded a strong 18.1 percent increase in new car sales in 2022, which "suggests that the market may have reached a saturation point, setting a high baseline for sluggish growth in 2023."\par \par \uc2 According to him, the challenging global macroeconomic conditions had pushed consumers to cheaper options, hence the rising motorcycle and used car sales.\par \par \uc2 "It is widely observed that, when faced with financial pressures, consumers often engage in belt-tightening, leading to shifts in \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  behavior," he said.\par \par \uc2 However, \uc2 Fitch Solutions\uc2  still projects growth in new car sales to 1.1 million units this year, supported by expected interest rate cuts, positive real wage growth, \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  certainty after the general election and low household debt levels.\par \par \uc2 Abrar Aulia, an industry and regional analyst at state-owned lender \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , also forecast new car sales between 1 million and 1.1 million units this year. Aside from the possible interest rate cut, the introduction of new models and the rising popularity of EVs will buoy purchases, according to him.\par \par \uc2 "There is a potential shift [from buying new to used cars] as the financing for used cars grew 30 percent last year. However, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown is still the major cause of the new car sales drop," Abrar said to the Post on Friday.\par \par \uc2 Electric growth\par \par \uc2 On Jan. 18, Chinese EV maker BYD launched three car models to mark its entrance into the largest market in Southeast Asia. It follows other EV manufacturers that have established a presence in Indonesia, such as South Korea's Hyundai and China's Wuling, DFSK, Chery and Neta.\par \par \uc2 In the following week, global investment firm \uc2 JP Morgan\uc2  downgraded its rating for publicly listed Astra Internasional from neutral to underweight, citing rising competition with BYD.\par \par \uc2 The local conglomerate, which distributes Japanese car brands like \uc2 Toyota\uc2  and \uc2 Daihatsu\uc2  in the country, is still the clear market leader with a 56 percent market share for new car sales last year. However, it seems reluctant to quickly move into the EV realm as it sticks with conventional and hybrid vehicles.\par \par \uc2 Robertus Hardy, head of research at Mirae Asset Sekuritas, opined that \uc2 Astra\uc2  may still perform well financially due to motorcycle sales but may see its growth in new car sales held back by BYD.\par \par \uc2 EVs still account for only a small portion of Indonesia's market. Last year, only 17,060 EVs were sold--a mere 1.7 percent of total new cars sold. \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  sees EV sales making up around 3.5 percent of total new passenger cars this year.\par \par \uc2 According to SISAPIRa, the government website that tracks the allocation of \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  for electric two-wheelers, 11.532 subsidized units were sold last year, and the Indonesian Electric Motorcycle Industry Association (Aismoli) estimates that overall EV bike sales may have been a little higher, at around 12,000.\par \par \uc2 The association does not have a sales projection for this year but is optimistic that the number will exceed the Industry Ministry's quota for 50,000 subsidized two-wheelers.\par \par \uc2 "In January, SISAPIRa recorded 8,800 applications [for the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ]. If only 5,000 of those requests are approved [each month], that means 60,000 electric motorcycle units would be sold this year," Aismoli secretary-general Hanggoro Ananta told the Post on Monday.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240130ek1v00005\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
