\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 MAINTAIN CONSUMPTION, INVESTMENT TO SUPPORT  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2  IN 2024: BI\b0\par\par\uc2 308 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 January 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Kenzu Tandiah\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesia must be able to maintain increasing consumption and investment to support \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2024, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  Deputy Governor Aida S. Budiman stated here on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 "According to our estimates, the composition of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will come from domestic demand. That way, Indonesia must be able to maintain consumption and investment," Budiman stated at the launch of the 2023 Indonesia \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Report.\par \par \uc2 She remarked that Indonesia needs to sustain the upward trend of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and synergy to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  optimism, resilience, and revival in 2024.\par \par \uc2 BI projected that Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2024 will grow by 4.7 percent to 5.5 percent, with stability maintained both internally and externally.\par \par \uc2 BI estimated that in the medium term, national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  improvement will continue with maintained stability, thereby supporting national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  revival towards realizing the vision of Advanced Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 2023 grew well and resilient amid the global slowdown and high \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  challenges in 2023 included weak \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth due to divergence, slow inflation decrease, long-term high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , capital outflows from emerging markets and developing economies (EMDEs), and the strong US dollar exchange rate.\par \par \uc2 In 2023, Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth was backed by domestic demand and is estimated to be in the range of 4.5 to 5.3 percent.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia"s foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  also increased to US$146.4 billion at the end of December 2023.\par \par \uc2 "Our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is (estimated to be) good, probably around five percent. Inflation is under control. The external sector is also good. We have US$146.4 billion in our foreign exchange reserve, and of course, this maintains our appreciated exchange rate," she remarked.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-KZU/B/Y012/Y012) 31-01-2024 17:01:56\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240131ek1v000m9\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  Anticipates Fed Rate Cuts in H2 2024 to Boost Rupiah\b0\par\par\uc2 365 \uc2 words\par \uc2 31 January 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. The rupiah is projected to strengthen in the latter half of 2024, reaching its fundamental level of Rp 15,000. This aligns with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's anticipation of a reduction in the benchmark interest rate by the \uc2 US Federal Reserve\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "The rupiah has experienced fluctuations, but there is confidence that it will appreciate towards its fundamentals in the second semester. Efforts will be made to maintain rupiah stability, and it is anticipated to strengthen," said BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 On Wednesday, the rupiah was traded at Rp 15,775 per dollar, marking a 5 percent depreciation compared to the same day last year.\par \par \uc2 BI anticipates a reduction in the \uc2 Federal Reserve\uc2 's interest rate in the second half of 2024.\par \par \uc2 "We estimate it might be in the second semester. God willing, it (rupiah) will ease after the Federal Fund Rate (FFR) goes down," said Perry.\par \par \uc2 Efforts to stabilize the rupiah exchange rate involve the implementation of a pro-market monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  through market mechanisms. BI is also collaborating with money market association institutions to deepen the financial market.\par \par \uc2 "We will continue to strengthen the mix of pro-stability monetary policies while observing opportunities in the second semester, whether there are possibilities of interest rate cuts and stabilizing the exchange rate," added Perry.\par \par \uc2 Previously, Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  predicted the rupiah exchange rate would remain stable with a tendency to strengthen, supported by the easing global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the decreasing trend of yields on bonds in major developed countries, and the diminishing pressure for the appreciation of the US dollar.\par \par \uc2 As of the end of December 2023, the rupiah's point-to-point exchange rate has strengthened by 1.11 percent year on year compared to the end of the previous year. This performance outperforms the Thai Baht and the Philippine Peso, which only strengthened by 0.76 percent and 0.62 percent year on year, respectively.\par \par \uc2 "Rupiah's appreciation is also supported by BI's stabilization policies and the resurgence of foreign portfolio inflows, in line with domestic financial asset yields and the positive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook for Indonesia," said Sri Mulyani.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020240131ek1v00005\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw2