\par\par \b \uc2 Weak exports,  \highlight22\uc2 spending \highlight\uc2  hit 2023 growth\b0\par\par\uc2 Deni Ghifari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 774 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 February 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  expanded at a much slower rate last year, with weaker household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and exports weighing on the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  output.\par \par \uc2 The country's GDP grew by 5.05 percent last year, much lower than the 5.31 percent logged the previous year, Statistics Indonesia (BPS) data show.\par \par \uc2 This figure also fell short of the 5.3 percent target stipulated in the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for last year, but it fell exactly in line with the Finance Ministry's projection for 2023 made in early January.\par \par \uc2 Interim BPS head Amalia Adininggar Widyasanti attributed the slowdown to slower growth in \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , particularly among upper-middle earners, as hinted by the much lower collection of luxury goods \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a decline in air travel and a drop in car sales last year.\par \par \uc2 "Meanwhile, financial investments like futures strengthened, indicating a slight shift from \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to investment," said Amalia\par \par \uc2 Growth in household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which contributed over half of the national GDP, dipped to 4.82 percent last year from 4.93 percent the year before.\par \par \uc2 The group saw its growth slide in the last three quarters from 5.22 percent in Q2 to 5.06 and 4.47 percent in Q3 and Q4, respectively.\par \par \uc2 Growth in exports, which contributed almost a quarter to the GDP, plummeted to just 1.32 percent last year amid a weaker global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and commodity prices, whereas the country had booked over 16 percent at one point in the previous year.\par \par \uc2 Coordinating \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Minister \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2  remained confident that the 2023 growth was still some of the highest in the world, pointing out that only a few countries had managed to reach that figure, citing China and the Philippines as examples.\par \par \uc2 According to the \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2 , world \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  output was projected to only grow by 3.1 percent last year, with developed countries expected to post almost half of the world's estimate.\par \par \uc2 Airlangga told reporters during a press briefing on Monday that the Indonesian people had resorted to increasing their savings due to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which was why the government was disbursing social assistance for lower-middle earners.\par \par \uc2 "This is so purchasing power can be maintained and therefore increase market confidence," said Airlangga.\par \par \uc2 However, Tauhid Ahmad, analyst at the Institute for Development of Economics and Finance (INDEF) told The Jakarta Post on Monday that lower consumption may imply weaker purchasing power in Indonesian households, which thereby leads to less \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Manufacturing, trade, agriculture, transportation and logistics, which combined contributed half of the GDP, booked weaker growth in 2023. Manufacturing, for instance, grew by only 4.64 percent from previously 4.89 percent in 2022.\par \par \uc2 The mining and construction sectors, which together contributed a fifth of the GDP, however, continue to grow at a faster pace in 2023 compared with the previous year.\par \par \uc2 Economist from private lender Bank Danamon, Irman Faiz, wrote in a statement on Monday that he expected household consumption to continue slowing down this year. The same went for exports.\par \par \uc2 Irman said investment, which was indicated by BPS' gross fixed capital formation (PMTB), had shown much better growth due to a flurry of government-led infrastructure projects last year.\par \par \uc2 This component, which contributed almost 30 percent of the GDP, grew by 4.4 percent, slightly faster than the 3.87 percent seen in the previous year.\par \par \uc2 However, he saw that the government's investments after the election on Feb. 14 may not be as robust as last year, citing the transition to the new administration as one of the factors.\par \par \uc2 Private lender Bank Permata chief economist Josua Pardede said in an analysis on Monday that the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown had dragged down international trade last year, which subsequently lowered commodity prices, thereby downing overall exports, including for Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 He said several major commodity prices had hit record highs in 2022, but last year, most of these were normalized despite remaining higher than the pre-pandemic level.\par \par \uc2 This trend would continue this year, he said, therefore potentially quenching this year's exports further.\par \par \uc2 Moreover, Josua said Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  faced risks stemming from food inflation due to the El Ni?o weather phenomenon, which would dampen household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  despite the government's efforts to mitigate the risks through social assistance.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the general election would cause investors to continue their wait-and-see approach, holding out for the result before realizing their investment.\par \par \uc2 The government has maintained that overall it could achieve 5.2 percent GDP growth this year, but both Josua and Irman expect far weaker growth, at 5.07 and 4.9 percent, respectively.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240205ek2600001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw177\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2655\pichgoal600
