\par\par \b \uc2 Unusual aid  \highlight22\uc2 spending \highlight\uc2  under fire ahead of polls\b0\par\par\uc2 Deni Ghifari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 633 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 February 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The government has recently acknowledged extending an ad hoc program that allows it to withhold 5 percent of ministry and agency budgets as a pool for emergent, undisclosed expenses, a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that some experts say may be funding increased aid \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the 2024 general election.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , known as "automatic adjustment", blocks out some Rp 50 trillion (US$3.17 billion) from this year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to a Finance Ministry circular letter obtained by The Jakarta Post dated Dec. 29, 2023.\par \par \uc2 Ministry spokesperson Deni Surjantoro told the Post on Friday that President \uc2 Joko "Jokowi" Widodo\uc2  had personally ordered the continuation of the program to serve as a buffer against the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  impacts of heightened geopolitical risk.\par \par \uc2 He added that the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had been used in the 2022 and 2023 state budgets. Two years ago, it allowed the government to spend more on fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid high international oil prices triggered by Russia's invasion of Ukraine.\par \par \uc2 But experts say there is little justification for continuing the program this year, as the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has performed relatively well over the past few years and global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  has lessened, as demonstrated by declining commodity prices and expectations of rate cuts from central banks.\par \par \uc2 At the same time, President \uc2 Joko "Jokowi" Widodo\uc2  has been disbursing social aid in person in a number of provinces and maintains that he is allowed to campaign for the candidate of his choice, a move that has drawn \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  scrutiny.\par \par \uc2 Deni of the Finance Ministry claimed the automatic adjustment funds were not for social aid, but he did not say what they were intended for.\par \par \uc2 Speaking to reporters on Monday, Coordinating Econo-mic Minister \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2  said the adjustment was "one of the methods" to make room for greater fertilizer \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  for farmers when asked whether it was used for social aid.\par \par \uc2 President Jokowi, meanwhile, has denied allegations that he has been using social aid distributions to advance his eldest son Gibran Rakabuming Raka's bid for the vice presidency, on the ticket of presidential candidate \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Politics in, prudence out\par \par \uc2 Center of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law Studies (CELIOS) executive director Bhima Yudhistira said there could be a connection between the "automatic adjustment" and the flurry of social aid this year.\par \par \uc2 "This has led to concerns that our \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  discipline is getting worse," Bhima told the Post on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 This year, the government earmarked Rp 496.8 trillion for social aid, a figure surpassing the allocations for the past few years and nearly on par with the record Rp 498 trillion worth of social aid distributed in 2020 amid the COVID-19 pandemic.\par \par \uc2 The 2024 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  does not mention anything about direct cash assistance (BLT) or rice distribution programs, both of which have continued from last year.\par \par \uc2 The government renewed a cash transfer program in January that granted Rp 200,000 per month to 18.8 million households until March. It said the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was intended to counter increased food prices.\par \par \uc2 The Finance Ministry's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  head, Febrio Nathan Kacaribu, said on Jan. 29 that the ministry would "look for" the money to fund the program, signaling that the financing source was still undecided.\par \par \uc2 Last year, the government disbursed similar aid in November and December 2023, citing El Ni?o's impact on food prices.\par \par \uc2 It also provided 10 kilograms of imported rice per month to some 21,000 households for much of last year, again citing El Ni?o. The program began in March 2023 and was supposed to last for three months but was extended multiple times and is now set to end in June of this year.\par \par \uc2 Continued on page 11\par \par \uc2 Related stories page 2, 4\par \par \uc2 Editorial page 6\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240206ek270000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
