\par\par \b \uc2 Indonesia Optimistic  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  to Grow to 5.2% in 2024\b0\par\par\uc2 285 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 February 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - The \uc2 Indonesian Finance Ministry\uc2  projected that the country\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will remain strong this year, taking into account global dynamics and the potential of the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIndonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is estimated to grow strongly by 5.2 percent in 2024,\u8221\'20\'1D the Finance Ministry\u8217\'20\'19s Head of the Communications and Information Services Bureau, Deni Surjantoro, said in his official statement on Wednesday, Feb. 7.\par \par \uc2 Since the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is anticipated to keep slowing down this year, Deni said the government would continue to monitor the risks.\par \par \uc2 The \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2  (\uc2 IMF\uc2 ) projected global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth at 3.1 percent in 2023 and 2024 in its World \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Outlook report in January 2024.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CAs for domestic factors, inflation is expected to be relatively stable. The impact of the elections on \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and government consumption and the housing sector \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rolled out in the fourth quarter of 2023 will be among the factors driving growth in 2024,\u8221\'20\'1D Deni explained.\par \par \uc2 He also said that the state revenue or APBN would serve as a shock absorber and be aimed at accelerating the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  transformation inclusively and sustainably.\par \par \uc2 Despite the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the Finance Ministry believed Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth would be more robust and stable. Although the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  started from a high base in 2022, it managed to record strong growth of 5.04 percent (yoy) in the fourth quarter of 2023 and 5.05 percent for the whole of 2023.\par \par \uc2 AMELIA RAHIMA SARI\par \par \uc2 Editor's Choice: Analyst Criticizes Presidential Candidates Overly Optimistic Growth Targets\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2023/11/22/id_1256703/1256703_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240207ek27000b7\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 The Risk of Automatic Adjustment of the State  \highlight22\uc2 Budget \highlight\uc2  for Jokowi\u8217\'20\'19s Social Assistance\b0\par\par\uc2 1,374 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 February 2024\par \uc2 Tempo Magazine\par \uc2 TEMGEN\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk. \par \par \uc2 NUR Janah seemed happy after receiving 10 kilograms of rice at the State Logistics Agency (Bulog) Warehouse, Klaten Regency, Central Java, on January 31. She is one of the food assistance\u8217\'20\'19s beneficiary families (KPM) in Klaten. President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  attended the food assistance distribution ceremony. \u8220\'20\'1CHe said the food aid is to help us because the price of rice has just risen,\u8221\'20\'1D she told Tempo on February 7.\par \par \uc2 Besides Nur Janah\u8217\'20\'19s family, there were 124,702 beneficiary families in Klaten. The Solo Bulog has also distributed rice to six other regions, including Solo City with 45,548 beneficiary families. One of them was Katino, a resident of the Sondakan, Laweyan subdistrict. He said he only received the rice in early February as the previous month\u8217\'20\'19s ration. \u8220\'20\'1CThe February-June ration is still waiting for information from the administrative village,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 Katino said he has been receiving 10 kilograms of rice since 2021. To enter the beneficiary families list, his information was recorded by his neighborhood chief. However, Katino revealed that there were differences in requirements and procedures when he received additional social assistance this time. If prior he only had to submit a copy of his identity card (KTP), this time he was asked to bring the original copy of his family card (KK). \u8220\'20\'1CThere was also a kind of form for accepting the aid,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 Chief of the Solo City Office of Agriculture, Food Resilience, and Fisheries, Eko Nugroho Isbandijarso, said that the January 2024 distribution of the assistance rice has been completed. According to him, there were more recipients because the current database was different from the previous social assistance database. There were 45,548 beneficiary families for this social assistance in Solo, compared to the 30,000 beneficiary families in the regular social assistance program. \u8220\'20\'1CWhat was used before was the Social Ministry\u8217\'20\'19s data, now it\u8217\'20\'19s data from the Coordinating Minister for Human Development and Culture,\u8221\'20\'1D said Eko.\par \par \uc2 President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  and Finance Minister Sri \uc2 Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  at the State Palace, Jakarta, December 7, 2016. TEMPO/Subekti\par \par \uc2 Rice assistance is part of the increasing flow of social assistance. Since the third quarter of 2023, the government has given various assistance, from 10 kilograms of rice for 20 million beneficiary families, to Rp400,000 (around US$25.5) of direct cash aid (BLT) for El Ni\u241\'00\'F1o. This is in addition to regular social assistance programs, such as the Family Hope Program and Non-Cash Food Assistance. This year, the government replaced the El Ni\u241\'00\'F1o direct cash aid with food risk mitigation cash assistance. The nominal has risen to Rp600,000 (US$38) from January to March, or Rp200,000 (US$12.7) per month for three months.\par \par \uc2 The new social assistance programs have forced Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  to set aside a special \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . In the 2024 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  for food risk mitigation cash assistance has reached Rp11.25 trillion (US$717.6 million). As a result, the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for social protection in the 2024 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  has increased by Rp20 trillion (US$1.3 billion) compared to the 2023 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , reaching a total of Rp496 trillion (US$31.6 billion).\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\par \par \uc2 THE statement by the Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Airlangga Hartarto on February 5, revealed the government\u8217\'20\'19s maneuver to allocate funds for social assistance this year. He mentioned that the funds resulting from the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  blockage of state ministries/agencies amounting to Rp50.14 trillion (US$3.2 billion) could be one of the funding sources for food risk mitigation direct cash assistance and other aids, such as fertilizer \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \u8220\'20\'1CThere are various techniques. The Finance Minister will handle it. One of them is automatic adjustment,\u8221\'20\'1D he said in his office.\par \par \uc2 The automatic adjustment Airlangga was referring to is the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s automatic revision through every ministry and state institution\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 spending reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  by temporarily blocking certain \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  items. Provisions for the automatic adjustment had actually been issued on December 29, 2023, through Finance Minister Circular No. S-1082/MK.02/2023. The letter signed by Minister Sri Mulyani set the automatic adjustment to Rp50.14 trillion. \u8220\'20\'1CIn accordance with the President\u8217\'20\'19s instructions at the submission of the 2024 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  implementation list and taking into account global geopolitical conditions,\u8221\'20\'1D said the letter.\par \par \uc2 The letter also specifies the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  items subject to the blockage, including expendable, non-urgent, or postponable expenditures on goods and capital originating from 10 \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  accounts, such as honoraria, meeting packages, operational and non-operational goods expenditures. However, certain budgets are exempted from the blockage, namely social assistance, general election budgets, the Nusantara Capital City \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , multi-year contract payments, and rice and corn production improvement programs.\par \par \uc2 Tempo\u8217\'20\'19s report, published on January 21, 2024, already mentioned the automatic adjustment strategy. As explained in the report, a Finance Ministry official said Sri Mulyani attempted to secure the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  from automatic adjustment so that it would not be tampered with for political purposes. Sri Mulyani did not comment on the issue, but Airlangga Hartarto\u8217\'20\'19s statement on February 5 provided clarity on the purpose of using the blocked \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is for social assistance and fertilizer \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Raden Pardede, a member of the Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s assistance team, said that the automatic adjustment is needed for urgent needs. \u8220\'20\'1CThe Finance Ministry is doing this on the President\u8217\'20\'19s order, the President\u8217\'20\'19s discretion. This \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is prepared as a precaution,\u8221\'20\'1D he told Tempo on February 8. According to Raden, the automatic adjustment is needed not only for social assistance, but also to mitigate the impacts of El Ni\u241\'00\'F1o. The amount of blocked \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  may increase if El Ni\u241\'00\'F1o lasts longer than predicted.\par \par \uc2 Deni Sujantoro, Head of the Communication and Information Bureau at the Finance Ministry, said the automatic adjustment is not a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  cut. According to him, the reserved \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  still remains within each ministry/agency or is set aside for emergency situations and urgent needs. The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  set aside by all ministries and institutions are not uniform. \u8220\'20\'1CAround 5 to 6 percent,\u8221\'20\'1D he said. The Finance Ministry claims that this scheme has proven successful in maintaining the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s resilience over the past few years, such as during the Covid-19 pandemic.\par \par \uc2 One of the institutions impacted by the automatic adjustment is the Energy and Mineral Resources Ministry. Energy Ministry Secretary-General, Dadan Kusdiana, gave examples of how the ministry\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is impacted by the automatic adjustment. \u8220\'20\'1CFor example, we reduce activities such as meetings or official travels that can be postponed,\u8221\'20\'1D he said on February 8. Dadan assured that the automatic adjustment would not cut programs or strategic activities that would impact the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \u8220\'20\'1CWhat we are doing is adjusting operational activities that can be postponed or reduced, volume-wise.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 However, some argue that the automatic adjustment mechanism is problematic. Managing Director of Political \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Studies, Anthony Budiawan, said that automatic adjustment violates the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Law and State Finance Law. According to him, state \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be regulated down to the unit organization, function, program, activity, and type of \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as stipulated in Article 15 paragraph 5 of the State Finance Law.\par \par \uc2 Anthony emphasized that the reallocation of \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  items can only be done through changes to the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  with the approval of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  (DPR). \u8220\'20\'1C\b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  reallocation without involving the DPR can only be done during the pandemic (2020-2022), using a government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in lieu of law,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 Anthony was referring to Government \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in lieu of Law No. 1/2020 on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and stability of the financial system for Covid-19 pandemic mitigation. Anthony said that the DPR should summon \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  for accountability.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the Research Manager of the National Secretariat of the Indonesian Forum for \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Transparency, Badiul Hadi, stated that the principle of automatic adjustment is to maintain the resilience of the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in responding to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \u8220\'20\'1CHowever, because it happens in an election year, it needs to be cautious not to be politicized,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2024/02/11/854281/854281_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2024/02/11/854282/854282_1200.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMGEN0020240212ek2b0000g\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
