\par\par \b \uc2 And now, back to business!\b0\par\par\uc2 650 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 February 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post,\par \par \uc2 The surprisingly vast lead \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  and Gibran Rakabuming Raka have taken in Wednesday's presidential election, as shown by pollsters' quick count projections, has been welcomed by the business community, mostly because we can all get back to work now.\par \par \uc2 While representatives from domestic and foreign associations queried by The Jakarta Post refrained from making political assessments, they expressed relief at the possibility of avoiding a runoff in June.\par \par \uc2 Quick counts are conducted by independent pollsters and do not reflect official results, due to be announced next month, so the campaigns of \uc2 Anies Baswedan\uc2  and Ganjar Pranowo have not conceded defeat.\par \par \uc2 Be that as it may, the picture that is emerging is clearer than anything surveys had suggested, and the expectation of a single-round election is reassuring for investors: They want to get on with business and not worry about who will be in charge of the country come October.\par \par \uc2 They may also be looking forward to Indonesian society returning to more fruitful \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  discourse about improving laws and regulations to support business activities and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development, especially after election debates that revolved around politics too much and too little around policies.\par \par \uc2 The fact that the election proceeded without serious disruption--or worse, riots--across the archipelago will be particularly reassuring for foreign investors, given that Indonesia is still a young democracy.\par \par \uc2 Much has been said and written over the past months about President \uc2 Joko "Jokowi" Widodo\uc2 's influence on the election. These include criticisms leveled at the incumbent for distributing social assistance during the campaign period and for showing tacit support for the Prabowo-Gibran ticket, as many believed that a head of state ought to maintain neutrality in an election to choose their successor.\par \par \uc2 But any semblance of impartiality went out the window when Prabowo picked Jokowi's eldest son as his running mate following the Constitutional Court's controversial ruling that added an exception to the age of candidacy.\par \par \uc2 A bitter aftertaste will also linger from the rift between Jokowi and the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI-P), the party that helped bring him to power.\par \par \uc2 These developments are now firmly in the past, however, and many businesspeople will be grateful to have at least one \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  behind them. Looking back on the election, they might conclude that it wasn't pretty, but at least it's over and done with.\par \par \uc2 That seemed to be the mood of the stock market when trading resumed on Thursday after the election day holiday: The \uc2 Indonesia Stock Exchange\uc2  (IDX) Composite gained 1.3 percent, outperforming other Asian markets.\par \par \uc2 That also suggests investors are happy with the quick counts pointing to a single-round victory for Defense Minister Prabowo and Jokowi's eldest son Gibran, who campaigned on a platform of continuity and hence, predictability rather than change.\par \par \uc2 Given that the Jokowi administration has received praise from many sides for its macroeconomic and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies, continuing them is deemed good for business, even if some of Prabowo's campaign promises raised concerns about \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and funding.\par \par \uc2 Prabowo's team even signaled that it would be comfortable with a significantly higher debt-to-GDP ratio to support \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity and his free school lunch program. Government bondholders will likely seek some reassurance that the future administration will not depart from the path of budgetary prudence, even if it does increase \b \highlight22\uc2 public spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Moreover, the quick count results suggest that key projects of the Jokowi administration, from the new capital city to the downstream mineral industry and electric vehicle factories, will continue.\par \par \uc2 The election had been viewed as a potential risk for long-term megaprojects, since convincing investors that government commitments would be maintained across a regime change is a key challenge in a democracy.\par \par \uc2 The prospect of closing the election chapter soon means we can all get back to business, finally.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240215ek2g00006\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Indonesia's Long and Winding Lame Duck Period\b0\par\par\uc2 664 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 February 2024\par \uc2 Tempo Magazine\par \uc2 TEMGEN\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk. \par \par \uc2 INDONESIA\u8217\'20\'19S financial markets are entering a dangerous, turbulent period. The general and presidential elections are indeed over. And most likely, as the quick count results show, \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  might be the winner in a single round. However, the market should be aware that political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  has just begun. Indonesia is entering a lame duck period that can make financial market sentiment wildly fluctuate.\par \par \uc2 Prabowo may have an early celebration. Prabowo must wait, though, until his power materializes. According to the constitution, Prabowo will formally take office as president on October 21, 2024, following the conclusion of \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s tenure. This is the lame duck period, to use political terminology. Even though Prabowo was elected, President Jokowi is still the official head of state.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s current lame duck period is relatively long. In the United States, with a more complex presidential election system, it lasts only about two months, from the general elections in November to the inauguration of the new president in January the following year. In Indonesia, a protracted lame duck phase can result in major legal problems because there are no clear regulations governing what departing presidents can and cannot do as their term draws to a close.\par \par \uc2 It is only a matter of political etiquette. The departing president should avoid making significant decisions with long-term effects during the lame duck era, since the next president might not agree with them. He/she is the one who must carry out the choice taken by the departing president and deal with the consequences. For example, if market fluctuations lead to a crisis, a lame duck government will be unable to address it effectively.\par \par \uc2 In addition to legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the upcoming lame duck period will be marked by intense struggles among political parties. There will be a multi-front tug-of-war, either for building coalitions to support the government or for lining up an opposition power base. The political map can change abruptly.\par \par \uc2 Understandably, in this country, there are no ideologies or major agendas that can help the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  comprehend the policies of political parties. Consequently, the market finds it extremely difficult to project with any degree of accuracy how the coalition or opposition will be put together over the next few months.\par \par \uc2 The main determinant of whether a party will ally or oppose another is a matter of sharing power and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  interests among its leaders. Unfortunately, these struggles often take place in closed rooms, away from \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  observation. Investors close to political elites may have access to privileged information, while others must rely on gossip. This information imbalance certainly can harm retail investors in the stock market or government bonds.\par \par \uc2 Another factor that could add to the market\u8217\'20\'19s distress is the possible dissolution of the incumbent government\u8217\'20\'19s supporting party coalition. This could happen sooner in the lame duck period, before Prabowo\u8217\'20\'19s inauguration. Last week, for example, rumors of the resignation of several professional ministers or those affiliated with the Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI-P) emerged again. A cabinet reshuffle, especially if it affects important positions such as the Finance Minister, could prompt investors to reassess various risk factors that could threaten their portfolio value.\par \par \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  might also be unable to endure the lame duck phase in a composed manner. It is possible that losing presidential candidates would sue the Constitutional Court (MK) over election outcomes. Additionally, there are growing claims from several civil society organizations that the presidential and general elections were not held in a fair and honest manner.\par \par \uc2 There is also a good chance that street protests may pick up steam in Indonesia. Students from several institutions staged massive protests in Yogyakarta just a few days prior to the election. The financial market will be pulled into even more dramatic instability during this lame duck era if the student\u8217\'20\'19s street parliament movement gains traction elsewhere.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2024/02/18/854844/854844_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMGEN0020240219ek2i0000j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal