\par\par \b \uc2 Prabowo's promises raise  \highlight22\uc2 fiscal \highlight\uc2  concerns\b0\par\par\uc2 Aditya Hadi, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 551 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 February 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Two major credit rating agencies, \uc2 Fitch Ratings\uc2  and \uc2 Moody's\uc2 , have raised concern that Prabowo Subianto's expensive campaign promises could result in more expansionary \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 As the presidential hopeful, Prabowo plans to realize those programs by increasing the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio, as well as setting up a new state revenue agency that would report directly to the president.\par \par \uc2 However, the rating agencies believe such reforms may take time, while the implementation of the pledges may be imminent.\par \par \uc2 Analysts warn that sudden increase in government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to swiftly fulfil all of Prabowo's promises could breach the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  cap, which is set by law at 3 percent of GDP.\par \par \uc2 They urge the former general to reveal the financing plans for his programs, as well as the potential impact on the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  position, to reassure markets.\par \par \uc2 In his election campaign, Prabowo promised several big-ticket programs, such as continuing the construction of the new capital city, increasing defense \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and raising \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  servants' salaries.\par \par \uc2 The centerpiece of his campaign, free school lunches and nutritional support for 82.9 million people, would require some Rp 400 trillion (US$30 billion) per year, according to Dedek Prayudi, spokesperson for the youth division of Prabowo's campaign team.\par \par \uc2 That is equivalent to 12 percent of the entire state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for this year and around 2 percent of the country's GDP.\par \par \uc2 Thomas Rookmaaker, head of Asia Pacific sovereign ratings at \uc2 Fitch Ratings\uc2 , saidPrabowo's plan added to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding the country's medium-term \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 He cited comments published by the firm in September last year thatindicated that a material rise in Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  debt burden would negatively affect its sovereign credit profile.\par \par \uc2 "Initially, our baseline scenario is for Indonesian government debt to continue its gradual declining path, with \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  deficits kept below 3 percent of the GDP. However, Prabowo's statements suggesting the country could sustain a significantly higher government debt-to-GDP ratio point to risks to our projections," he told The Jakarta Post on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Rookmaaker acknowledged that Prabowo also promised to increase the revenue-to-GDP ratio to around 23 percent, which would enhance \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  finance flexibility and strengthen the country's credit profile. However, according to him, there is no clear plan on how the presidential hopeful aims to achieve that.\par \par \uc2 "Experience suggests that raising the state revenue-to-GDP ratio may not be that easy, and such reforms may take considerable time," Rookmaaker noted.\par \par \uc2 Moody's\uc2  also stated that some of Prabowo's pledges could indicate the pursuit of a more expansionary \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stance. If implemented, those programs would mark a divergence from Indonesia's long track record of conservatively managed budgetary finances and debt ratios.\par \par \uc2 "At this juncture, implications for sovereign creditworthiness are still neutral, although we will keenly watch the composition of parliament for greater clues on \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  direction and reform implementation," said Anushka Shah, senior credit officer at \uc2 Moody's\uc2  Investors Service, in a statement.\par \par \uc2 Clarity needed\par \par \uc2 According to Bhima Yudhistira, executive director of the Center of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law Studies (CELIOS), the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 -to-GDP ratio may surge to 5 percent in the worst-case scenario should Prabowo decide to be aggressive in \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Continued on page 11\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240221ek2m0000e\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw177\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2655\pichgoal600
