\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 BE CAREFUL WHILE SETTING  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  GROWTH TARGET: PRESIDENT\b0\par\par\uc2 334 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 February 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Raka Adji Putra\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - President Joko Widodo (Jokowi) called on ministries and institutions to exercise caution while setting an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target against global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  risks, such as recessions.\par \par \uc2 \u8221\'20\'1DAnticipation in creating growth target must reflect carefulness but (with) optimism, and credibility must also be maintained,\u8221\'20\'1D he remarked at the State Palace, Jakarta, on Monday.\par \par \uc2 Jokowi made the statement during a Plenary Cabinet Meeting for Ramadan and Eid al-Fitr Preparations, Government Work Programs, Macroeconomic Framework, and the Main Points of the 2025 \b \highlight22\uc2 Fiscal Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In his opening remarks, President Jokowi highlighted the situation and risks of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that affect the macroeconomic framework of 2025.\par \par \uc2 He pointed out that the economies of several countries, such as the UK and Japan, had entered recession.\par \par \uc2 To this end, he called on his cabinet to anticipate this aspect by setting an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target carefully while still being optimistic and credible.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, the president urged the central and regional governments to step up the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and prepare a contingency plan against \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil and recession.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CEnhance the focus of central and regional governments by preparing an alternative plan if there is turmoil and crisis,\u8221\'20\'1D he emphasized.\par \par \uc2 Japan\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has fallen into recession after it contracted in the third and fourth quarters of last year.\par \par \uc2 According to data from the Japanese government on Thursday (February 15), the country\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  shrank at an annual rate of 0.4 percent during the October-December period due to weak \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  power.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, according to data from the \uc2 Office for National Statistics\uc2 , the UK\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  contracted by 0.1 percent in the third quarter of 2023. The negative \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance continued in the fourth quarter of 2023, with a decline of 0.3 percent.\par \par \uc2 Earlier, on February 5, Statistics Indonesia (BPS) announced that Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  had grown by 5.05 percent in 2023.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-RAP/B/A043/A043) 26-02-2024 13:56:29\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240226ek2q0002t\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 News\par \b \uc2 Jokowi Urges Ministers to Prepare for Rising Food Price and Eid Exodus Ahead of Ramadan\b0\par\par\uc2 346 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 February 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. President \uc2 Joko "Jokowi" Widodo\uc2  discussed food price stability, preparations for the Eid exodus (mudik), and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies for 2025 during a cabinet meeting with ministry and agency leaders at the State Palace on Monday.\par \par \uc2 "As we enter March, we are approaching Ramadan, and in April, we will celebrate Eid al-Fitr. I urge all relevant ministries and agencies to be vigilant and ensure that the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  can worship peacefully and devoutly," said Jokowi.\par \par \uc2 The President highlighted the government's role in ensuring a peaceful worship environment, particularly through monitoring the stability of prices and the availability of food stocks, especially basic commodities.\par \par \uc2 "Also, accelerate the distribution of all social protection and social safety net packages," added Jokowi.\par \par \uc2 Earlier, the Indonesian Traditional Market Traders Association (Ikappi) revealed that market traders' revenue had plummeted by up to 50 percent due to the recent increase in rice prices reaching up to Rp 18,000 ($1.15) per kilogram.\par \par \uc2 The President also urged relevant ministries to adequately prepare infrastructure and transportation modes for the annual exodus (mudik).\par \par \uc2 In 2023, the Transportation Ministry estimated that 123 million people embarked on the annual exodus or approximately half of Indonesia's population.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, Jokowi mentioned that the meeting also addressed the government's work plan and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies for 2025, even though his terms end in October. The potential successor, Defense Minister \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2 , has consistently expressed his commitment to continuing Jokowi's agendas if elected.\par \par \uc2 "Even though we are waiting for the official election results from the \uc2 General Election Commission (KPU)\uc2 , the 2025 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft must be prepared because the elected president will implement it," he said.\par \par \uc2 In the context of the 2025 macroeconomic outlook, Jokowi urged the ministries to exercise caution regarding global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , while remaining optimistic and realistic in setting growth targets.\par \par \uc2 "With several countries already entering into recession, we need to exercise caution and credibility in setting growth targets and formulate plans to address possible upheavals and crises," concluded Jokowi.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020240226ek2q0000a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
