\par\par \b \uc2 Jokowi Says Indonesia Safe from  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  Recession Amid Sluggish Global  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 359 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 February 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  or Jokowi said the chances of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession in Indonesia are still very small. According to the president, the probability of sluggish \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity in the country is much lower than in large countries such as the United States, the UK, and Japan.\par \par \uc2 "We should be grateful, Indonesia's [recession] probability is still at 1.5 percent. This is what we must protect," said Jokowi on Wednesday, as broadcasted by the Presidential Secretariat.\par \par \uc2 He said this figure was much lower than other countries that are likely to experience an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recession soon. \u8220\'20\'1CThe probability of a recession has hit developed countries. For example, Germany is already at 72 percent. The E is also at 60 percent, while the United States is at 40 percent," Jokowi explained.\par \par \uc2 According to the president, several factors influence the sluggish global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including armed conflicts in several regions which led to sharp \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  adjustments for war.\par \par \uc2 In addition, Jokowi said that many countries implemented food protection policies, which recently hit 1,348 policies. That number has tripled in a decade, \u8220\'20\'1Cand this will continue to increase\u8221\'20\'1D, the president warned.\par \par \uc2 Even so, Jokowi claimed that Indonesia still succeeded in maintaining a strong national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . "Praise be to God, in the midst of continuous world crises, hard-to-calculate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains sturdy and considered the top three economies with good \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth based on G20," he said.\par \par \uc2 He also claimed that Indonesia has succeeded in reducing the Gini ratio to 0.388 percent. Meanwhile, the poverty rate fell by 9.36 percent, the unemployment rate fell by 5.32 percent, and the inflation rate was at 2.57 percent.\par \par \uc2 "Even though we see good numbers, I need to remind you that we have to be careful, we have to remain vigilant, because of the growing complexity of future global competition," the president remarked.\par \par \uc2 SULTAN ABDURRAHMAN\par \par \uc2 Editor's Choice: Indonesia Reconsiders to Issue Samurai Bonds Amid Japan Recession\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2024/02/28/id_1283228/1283228_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240229ek2t000dz\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b \uc2 Indonesia's  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  Chief Addresses \uc2 World Bank\uc2 's Concerns Over Free Lunch Program\b0\par\par\uc2 315 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 March 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. Chief \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Minister \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2  has addressed the recent comments from the \uc2 World Bank\uc2  regarding the potential impact of the free lunch program on the 2025 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (APBN).\par \par \uc2 Responding to the \uc2 World Bank\uc2 's mention of a 3 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Airlangga stated, "Who said the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be 3 percent? The Bank doesn't even know the details of the program," Airlangga said at his office in Jakarta on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 Airlangga emphasized that discussions with the \uc2 World Bank\uc2  on Tuesday focused on the opportunities and challenges of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  amidst global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , without delving into the financial implications of the programs.\par \par \uc2 During the meeting, Airlangga mentioned that discussions revolved around the projected \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the 2025 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , ranging between 2.4 percent and 2.8 percent.\par \par \uc2 In a related development, the Indonesian government conducted a trial run of the nationwide free meal program initiated by the projected winner of the presidential election, \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2 . The trial featured a menu consisting of chicken rice, boiled egg rice, siomay (fish cake), and gado-gado (salads with spicy peanut sauce).\par \par \uc2 The proposed \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the program is approximately Rp 15,000 ($1) per child per day, excluding the provision of milk. The program aims to cover around 82.9 million students gradually until 2029, with an estimated \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Rp 400 trillion ($25.5 billion).\par \par \uc2 The \uc2 World Bank\uc2  has advised caution in implementing the president's free lunch program, urging Indonesia to adhere to the specified upper limit of the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 3 percent of GDP, as mandated by law, to maintain macroeconomic and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability. Satu Kahkonen, the Head of the \uc2 World Bank\uc2  Representative for Indonesia and Timor-Leste, emphasized the importance of measured execution, considering both cost and resource availability, for the estimated Rp 400 trillion program cost.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020240301ek310000a\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Prabowo, Please Learn from Egypt\u8217\'20\'19s Trouble\b0\par\par\uc2 661 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 March 2024\par \uc2 Tempo Magazine\par \uc2 TEMGEN\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk. \par \par \uc2 POLITICAL upheaval and the disputed outcome of the general and presidential elections continue to cast a shadow over Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s financial markets. Investors are in a holding pattern, waiting for clarity amid the ongoing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Nevertheless, the current market sentiment is cautiously optimistic. The political turbulence is expected to subside soon, paving the way for a new government by October.\par \par \uc2 According to the quick count results and manual calculations by the \uc2 General Election Commission (KPU)\uc2 , which have now reached nearly three-quarters of the total votes, \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  is likely to lead Indonesia until 2029. As for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the market anticipates there will be little deviation from the policies already implemented by President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Nevertheless, one critical question remains unanswered: what will be the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Prabowo\u8217\'20\'19s future government? The cornerstone of Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability over the past three years has been the maintenance of prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies that has allowed the country to weather global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil successfully. Despite a brief spike during the pandemic, the government has managed to reduce the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 -to-gross domestic product (GDP) ratio below the legal limit of three percent.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  ratio even plummeted to an impressive 1.65 percent last year, serving as the bedrock of market confidence in Indonesia. Much of this success can be attributed to the steadfast leadership of Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2 . She has been vigilantly curbing frivolous \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  that does not contribute to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 Prabowo, on the contrary, does have a different view. On various occasions, he has stated that Indonesia can still bear a larger debt burden. He believes that the current \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 -to-GDP ratio is still too low. He wants a more aggressive \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to fund his programs.\par \par \uc2 Should Prabowo decide to pursue a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of larger deficits, market confidence will undoubtedly weaken. The first signs of this have already emerged. Interestingly, it was not Prabowo who initiated this move, but rather President Jokowi, who took the initiative to prepare one of Prabowo\u8217\'20\'19s programs, namely free lunch. Jokowi even convened a cabinet meeting to discuss the funding for this program, which is set to be included in the 2025 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  currently being drafted by the government. This program is estimated to cost up to two percent of GDP each year, making it a significant financial commitment.\par \par \uc2 Excessive government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  has the potential to inflate the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  and trigger an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn. To grasp the gravity of this \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  principle, Prabowo could examine Egypt\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is teetering on the edge of bankruptcy. Over the past two years, the value of Egypt\u8217\'20\'19s currency has plummeted by over 50 percent, from 15 to 31 Egyptian pounds per United States dollar. In Egypt\u8217\'20\'19s black market, the price of the US dollar has even reached twice the official rate, indicating severe \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  instability.\par \par \uc2 The heart of these challenges stems from an escalating \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  aimed at subsidizing various sectors. In a parallel to Indonesia, Egypt is undertaking a colossal project to construct a new capital city, estimated at a staggering US$58 billion.\par \par \uc2 Consequently, the Egyptian government is grappling with substantial high-interest dollar debt. The situation reached a critical juncture when conflict erupted in Gaza and ship traffic in the \uc2 Suez Canal\uc2  dwindled. This led to a sharp drop in foreign currency inflows and the depletion of Egypt\u8217\'20\'19s foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Presently, Egypt is banking on the implementation of a pledged US$35 billion investment from the United Arab Emirates and a US$10 billion loan from the \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2  (\uc2 IMF\uc2 ) to stave off the specter of bankruptcy.\par \par \uc2 Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is presently on a stable trajectory. However, should Prabowo persist in executing ambitious, populist, and expensive initiatives, the nation risks mirroring Egypt\u8217\'20\'19s financial missteps within the next two to three years, potentially leading to the looming threat of bankruptcy.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2024/03/03/855869/855869_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMGEN0020240304ek330000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichg