\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 FUEL PRICE RETAINED FOR SUSTAINED GROWTH OF PEOPLE'S  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2 : MINISTER\b0\par\par\uc2 352 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 March 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Minister of State-owned Enterprises Erick Thohir stated that the government is keen to maintain the growth of the people"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  by not increasing the price of fuel in the near future.\par \par \uc2 The rising rice prices in several regions, which increase the people"s burden, is one of the reasons that the government decided to retain the current fuel price, he explained.\par \par \uc2 "We retain the current fuel (price) to ensure the people"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  keep growing, and the people"s burden will not increase," Thohir stated here on Monday.\par \par \uc2 The minister affirmed that the government is toiling to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  balance to ensure the residents" purchasing power is not affected by the ongoing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "We should ensure that residents in the lowest \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  level are not affected by it. We are trying to balance it and are convinced that our inflation and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will be under control," Thohir affirmed.\par \par \uc2 However, he admitted that adjustments to the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  are required to hold the current fuel price until June 2024.\par \par \uc2 "Yes, (\b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) adjustment is a certainty, but as long as all ministries cooperate to implement policies that will benefit the people, we must not look at its profits or losses. We should prioritize maintaining Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability," the minister remarked.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, President Joko Widodo (Jokowi), before departing for Australia to attend the ASEAN-Australia Special Summit on Monday, confirmed that the price of fuel oil (BBM) would not increase in the near future.\par \par \uc2 "It won"t go up," President Jokowi stated when asked about the possibility of an increase in fuel prices.\par \par \uc2 Coordinating Minister of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2  on February 26 also affirmed that apart from the fuel prices, the electricity rate will not increase until June 2024.\par \par \uc2 Hartarto stated that an additional \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be disbursed to state-owned oil company \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  and electricity company PT PLN to allow the prices to stand at the current rate.\par \par \uc2 (T.N015/A/Y012/Y012) 04-03-2024 16:02:05\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240304ek34000m9\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
