\par\par \b \uc2 Analysis: Investment opportunities and challenges in priority sectors\b0\par\par\uc2 1,060 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 March 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Reny Eka Putri, Mandiri, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The conditions and prospects of investment in Indonesia are topics that continue to be of interest this year. Investment is a crucial factor supporting \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and vital to sustainable development.\par \par \uc2 With a large population and stable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth amid high global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Indonesia can attract the interest of domestic and foreign investors to invest in various \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sectors.\par \par \uc2 This investment can help create jobs, increase per capita income and expand \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  opportunities for the community.\par \par \uc2 Along with global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  developments, Indonesia strives to increase its investment competitiveness through various policies and initiatives.\par \par \uc2 The Indonesian government has implemented various \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and non-\b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives to encourage investment, including simplifying regulations, improving infrastructure and improving the investment climate.\par \par \uc2 Apart from that, Indonesia is also aggressively promoting investment in various countries through participation in international forums and holding various investment promotion events.\par \par \uc2 In 2023, the Investment Ministry/Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM) recorded that investment realization throughout 2023 reached Rp 1.41 quadrillion (US$89.59 billion).\par \par \uc2 This achievement exceeded the target (101.3 percent) previously set at Rp 1.4 quadrillion with total employment of 1,823,543 people. Realized investment in 2023 consisted of realized foreign direct investment (FDI) amounting to Rp 744 trillion, equivalent to 52.4 percent of total investment realization, and realized domestic investment (DDI) amounting to Rp 674.9 trillion or reaching 47.6 percent.\par \par \uc2 The realization of this investment grew by 17.5 percent year-on-year (yoy) compared with the 2022 achievement, which only reached Rp 1.2 quadrillion.\par \par \uc2 Investment realization throughout 2023 spread across five main sectors: the basic metal industry, metal goods, non-machinery and equipment; transportation, warehouse and telecommunications; mining; housing, industrial and office areas and the chemical and pharmaceutical industries.\par \par \uc2 Apart from accelerating investment projects that are already underway, to promote investment in support of the development of the the new capital city Nusantara, the Investment Ministry/BKPM is holding the launch of 12 Investment Opportunity Map (PPI) projects in 2023.\par \par \uc2 The total value of the investment from the 12 projects offered is Rp 52.17 trillion.\par \par \uc2 Investment in 2024 is targeted to be higher at Rp 1.6 quadrillion. In line with developments and needs, Indonesian investment is not limited to traditional sectors such as agriculture, mining and manufacturing.\par \par \uc2 Still, it is also increasingly expanding into innovative sectors such as information technology, renewable energy and start-ups.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia has great potential to become an attractive investment destination for investors looking for long-term growth opportunities.\par \par \uc2 Priority sectors in investment\par \par \uc2 Long-term investment projects are crucial in Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and cover key sectors such as infrastructure, energy, agriculture and tourism.\par \par \uc2 There are projects in priority investment sectors in Indonesia, such as the infrastructure sector, including the construction of roads, airports, ports and other transportation networks, which aim to increase connectivity and mobility within the country.\par \par \uc2 Apart from that, the energy sector also has very high investment potential. As a developing country with a large population, energy demand continues to increase along with \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and urbanization.\par \par \uc2 Investment in the energy sector, especially in renewable energy and energy efficiency, is crucial to ensure a sustainable and environmentally friendly supply. Apart from that, this sector also broadly impacts infrastructure development and other industries. The government states that Indonesia currently has a new renewable energy (EBT) potential of 3,600 gigawatts and is also building a Green Industrial Park covering an area of 30 thousand hectares.\par \par \uc2 With abundant natural resources, Indonesia has great potential to develop renewable energy sources such as geothermal and solar energy.\par \par \uc2 The manufacturing sector is also an attractive priority sector for investors. With a large population and strong consumer growth, Indonesia's manufacturing industry has immense market potential. Investment in the development of the manufacturing industry can help increase added value in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , create jobs and encourage the growth of other sectors, such as distribution and logistics.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, investment opportunities in manufacturing focus on three Indonesian export commodities: automotives, textiles and footwear.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, investment opportunities for the tourist sector are focused on developing priority development and branding goals for Indonesian tourism (Lake Toba, Mandalika, Labuan Bajo, Borobudur, Joglo Semar, Bali, Jakarta, Banyuwangi, Bromo and the Riau Islands).\par \par \uc2 No less important, the information and communications technology sector is also a promising priority sector for investors. Indonesia has an increasingly connected and digital-based population, creating enormous opportunities for developing applications, e-commerce platforms and other digital services. Investments in the technology sector can help accelerate digital transformation in various industries, improve operational efficiency and expand market reach.\par \par \uc2 Investment development in Indonesia has shown positive growth in recent years, driven by factors such as macroeconomic stability, structural reforms and government policies supporting investment.\par \par \uc2 Investor confidence will remain with the prospect of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth remaining solid in 2024 at around 5 percent. In allocating investment in priority sectors, investors need to consider factors such as supportive regulations, available infrastructure and the availability of skilled labor.\par \par \uc2 Investors can significantly contribute to Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development by choosing priority sectors with high growth potential and supporting sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development.\par \par \uc2 Challenges also remain in efforts to increase Indonesian investment. Some of these include infrastructure that still needs to be improved, complex bureaucracy, a lack of workforce skills and regulatory \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 To overcome this challenge, collaboration between the government, private sector and academic institutions is important to creating a conducive and sustainable investment environment.\par \par \uc2 With solid commitment and cross-sectoral cooperation, Indonesian investment has great potential to continue growing and benefit the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development. Indonesia must continue implementing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms and improving the investment climate to attract more investment and achieve inclusive and also sustainable growth.\par \par \uc2 The implications of investment conditions in Indonesia have a significant impact, especially in increasing the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  competitiveness in the global market.\par \par \uc2 By encouraging investment in strategic sectors and reducing investment barriers, Indonesia can strengthen its position as an attractive investment destination for foreign investors.\par \par \uc2 One of the efforts taken by \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  to encourage the investment climate is holding the Mandiri Investor Forum 2024, which succeeded in attracting more than 25,000 participants from various countries. We hope this international-scale event can increase Indonesian investment to encourage more robust \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the future.\par \par \uc2 _____________________\par \par \uc2 Senior quantitative analyst at \uc2 Bank Mandiri\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240305ek3600002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
