\par\par \b \uc2 Global gold price spike a new impetus to boost gold production\b0\par\par\uc2 818 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 April 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Edi Permadi\uc2  , Jakarta\par \par \uc2 Article 33 (1) of the 1945 Constitution mandates that Indonesia's land, water and natural riches shall be controlled by the state and exploited to the greatest benefit of the people.\par \par \uc2 Gold \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  are included in the above article, which should be implemented with national interests in mind. Based on the Constitutional Court ruling, the "shall be controlled by the State" clause is interpreted as five principles or functions.\par \par \uc2 The state has a mandate to issue licenses while managing and supervising the related industries to benefit the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The local gold price according to Logam Mulia today is Rp 1,195,983 (US$75.31) per gram, marking a huge jump compared to January 2023, when the price was Rp 1,026,000 per gram, and is significantly higher than Rp 970,000 per gram in 2020. The 16 percent increase since January 2023 has provided a lucrative investment opportunity for personal portfolios.\par \par \uc2 Companies involved in the gold industry will also see an additional upside in 2024 because of rising gold prices.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia, a mineral resource-rich country, is ranked sixth in the world for its \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to the \uc2 United States Geological Survey\uc2 . Identified worldwide \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  gold \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  currently stand at 52,000 tonnes. The survey states that Indonesia has 2,600 tonnes of gold \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 . They also described \uc2 PT Freeport Indonesia\uc2  as one of the biggest reserve holders in the world.\par \par \uc2 There were 124 mining licenses (IUP) and 25 Contracts of Work (CoW) issued in 2020, with yearly production based on the 2020 estimation of 65 tonnes of gold.\par \par \uc2 There are three gold production lines in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 The first is through the IUP and CoW process. This is a legal mining process, and the products are mostly refined by Logam Mulia PT ANTAM.\par \par \uc2 The second one is copper and gold miners like \uc2 PT Freeport Indonesia\uc2  (PTFI), which produces concentrate that is mostly exported. PTFI is now building a large smelter facility in Gresik, East Java, and will start production in August of this year.\par \par \uc2 The thirdis community mining production through special licenses for small-scale mining. The main problem for this category is environment and safety concerns, as community mining often falls below industry standards. Royalty payments poser another issue as most of the production goes to gold stores.\par \par \uc2 There is also a challenge with the real resource and reserve statement for the third line because it is close to nothing. However, there are large potential resources in Gorontalo and Maluku.\par \par \uc2 The conflict between the first and third production lines continues to escalate. The Energy and Mineral Resources Ministry has managed this problem to reduce the overlap between those production lines. On the ground, however, conflicts remain prevalent.\par \par \uc2 The collaboration between the energy ministry--with the first and the second production lines--and the Industry Ministry as a license issuer for processing in the third production line should be more effective. Synergy between the first, second and third production lines can help to avoid conflict and ensure proper environmental management and safety standards for all production lines. It can also improve royalty, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and nontax government income.\par \par \uc2 Giants like PTFI and Mind ID can develop sustainable growth projects by expanding smelter facilities and stepping up the production stage for high capital \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  underground projects such as the Kucing Liar project.\par \par \uc2 For a low-cost oxide gold producer like PT J Resources Asia Pacific, this is a great opportunity to produce more gold by constructing a brownfield project.\par \par \uc2 PT Antam will increase their production in Pongkor and Cibaliung and increase productivity for the Logam Mulia refinery by increasing its capacity to accept refinery jobs from national miners.\par \par \uc2 Mining investment needs huge capital and access to financial support, high-quality human resources, management and mature technology applications to comply with global and national standards and regulations.\par \par \uc2 Gold demand is increasing significantly amid global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as gold is considered one of the safest investments during worldwide upheavals and conflicts such as the wars in Ukraine and Gaza.\par \par \uc2 Geopolitical instability between Russia and \uc2 NATO\uc2  has turned Ukraine into a proxy battleground. Russia is the 12th largest consumer of gold, and now people are moving to the mineral as a safe-haven investment. Germany, the fourth largest gold consumer, is also looking for additional gold.\par \par \uc2 The Middle East is on fire and the war in Gaza has triggered rising demand for gold.\par \par \uc2 Saudi Arabia, Iran, the United Arab Emirates and Turkey are also looking for gold, especially jewelry, for their investments.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, China and the US are both looking for gold to further their investments in the mineral.\par \par \uc2 This is the right time for the government to boost gold production. However, they must eliminate major obstacles that face gold miners.\par \par \uc2 ______________________\par \par \uc2 The author is a natural resources expert at th