\par\par \b \uc2 OJK Announces End of COVID-19 Banking Credit Relaxation\b0\par\par\uc2 388 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 April 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - The \uc2 Financial Services Authority (OJK)\uc2  announced on Sunday that the banking credit relaxation \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which was provided to ease the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic, has ended on March 31, 2024.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe end of the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is in line with the revocation of the COVID-19 pandemic status by the government in June 2023,\u8221\'20\'1D Chair of the OJK Board of Commissioners Mahendra Siregar said on Sunday, March 31, 2024.\par \par \uc2 Apart from that, he said, the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been ended by taking into account Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition which has recovered from the impact of the pandemic.\par \par \uc2 The OJK assessed that Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s banking sector currently has a strong resilience in facing the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  dynamics, supported by strong capital, sufficient liquidity, and good risk management.\par \par \uc2 To this end, the banking sector is deemed ready to face the end of the COVID-19 credit relaxation \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 This is also supported by the continuing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery with an inflation rate that is under control and investment that is growing.\par \par \uc2 In line with the revocation of the COVID-19 pandemic status in Indonesia in June 2023, the community\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities continue to grow.\par \par \uc2 The credit relaxation \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which took effect in early 2020, had been utilized by many debtors, especially micro, small, and medium enterprises (MSMEs).\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was part of the countercyclical \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a landmark \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in supporting the performance of debtors, banking, and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in general to get through the pandemic period.\par \par \uc2 Various indicators in January 2024 showed that Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s banking sector was in good condition.\par \par \uc2 They include the Capital Adequacy Ratio (CAR) at 27.54 percent, Liquidity Coverage Ratio (LCR) at 231.14 percent, Non-Core Deposit (NCD) at 123.42 percent, and an adequate level of profitability.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThis is expected to be a solid cushion to mitigate risks amid the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions,\u8221\'20\'1D Siregar remarked.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the credit quality has been maintained below the 5 percent threshold, with the gross nonperforming loan (NPL) at 2.35 percent and net NPL at 0.79 percent.\par \par \uc2 ANTARA\par \par \uc2 Editor's Choice: OJK Issues Rule on Islamic Banking; Mandates Sharia Governance Now Mandatory to Industry Actors\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2019/05/17/id_842466/842466_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240401ek4100002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
