\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIA EXPECTS WWF TO BUILD POLITICAL CONSENSUS ON CLIMATE CHANGE\b0\par\par\uc2 430 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 April 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Resinta Sulistiyandari\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesia"s Meteorology, Climatology, and Geophysics Agency (BMKG) is optimistic that the 10th World Water Forum (WWF) in Bali will generate political consensus among participating heads of state on overcoming the challenge of the climate crisis.\par \par \uc2 The forum is scheduled to take place from May 18\u8211\'20\'1325, 2024,\par \par \uc2 At an online seminar on Monday, BMKG head Dwikorita Karnawati said that based on the results of analyses by world climate institutions, current climate and weather conditions continue to be \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including due to the uncontrolled release of the greenhouse gas CO2 in the atmosphere.\par \par \uc2 Climate \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  can result in the emergence of extreme weather events, such as drought and rain above the normal average, which can lead to social and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  health degradation and affect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions of a country.\par \par \uc2 "This is one of the important substances for WWF in Bali because most countries in the world have felt the impact of climate change, which means that water availability must be maintained for the common good," Karnawati said.\par \par \uc2 According to her, the forum will also produce a political consensus from representatives of 30 participating countries with a binding decision that will have to be implemented to overcome the potential of the climate crisis.\par \par \uc2 This binding consensus will be the most important outcome of the forum since it will reflect the agreement of all participants to execute all action plans that have been prepared scientifically, based on ecosystems and natural events, by their respective countries, she informed.\par \par \uc2 She said that the real action plan will mitigate climate change and eradicate the gap between the challenges and capacities of each country in terms of managing water resources, climate, food, energy, and health.\par \par \uc2 "Each country has different capabilities in handling this matter. The lack of knowledge in science and technology makes the gap even more complex. Now, we can end it by working together to tackle the climate crisis," she added.\par \par \uc2 The 10th World Water Forum bears the theme "Water for Shared Prosperity," which translates into six sub-themes: water for humans and nature; water security and prosperity; disaster risk reduction and mitigation; governance cooperation and hydro diplomacy; sustainable water finance; and knowledge and innovation.\par \par \uc2 At the forum, Indonesia will convene discussions between stakeholders from several regions, namely the Mediterranean, Asia-Pacific, America, and Africa along with member countries of the \uc2 World Water Council\uc2 , to identify mechanisms and approaches to resolve water-related issues.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-RST/A/Y012/Y012) 01-04-2024 19:19:56\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240401ek41000ul\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Political  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty \highlight\uc2  Disrupting Financial Markets\b0\par\par\uc2 621 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 April 2024\par \uc2 Tempo Magazine\par \uc2 TEMGEN\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk. \par \par \uc2 INDONESIA is currently in the midst of political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . On March 20, the General Election Commission declared \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  as the president-elect. However, Prabowo must patiently wait for seven more months before officially entering the State Palace as the President of the Republic of Indonesia on October 20. His waiting game may be uncertainly prolonged further if the Constitutional Court upholds disputes regarding his victory in the election.\par \par \uc2 This relatively long waiting period has the potential to create numerous complications in \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making process. \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  officially remains the president. His decisions during his lame-duck period will undoubtedly have implications for the future, burdening Prabowo\u8217\'20\'19s administration with the consequences. Meanwhile, Prabowo may not necessarily agree with Jokowi\u8217\'20\'19s choices in deciding those policies.\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  options that could potentially be controversial are beginning to emerge into the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  domain. For example, the new capital city development project. Soedrajad Djiwandono, former Governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  and one of Prabowo\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  advisors, stated that the implementation of the free lunch program promised by Prabowo during his campaigns is more important than the development of a new capital city.\par \par \uc2 This viewpoint is in stark contrast to Jokowi\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which aggressively promotes the construction of a new capital city. The allocation of funds for this landmark project has always been a priority for his government and must not be disrupted. The government is also not hesitant to issue various regulations to provide incentives for the private sector to invest in it. It is worth noting that this project has yet to attract major foreign investors.\par \par \uc2 There is an irony in contradicting these two policies. Both have serious flaws that create controversies. Building a grand new palace in the midst of forests and on peatlands is clearly a wrong choice if the government indeed intends to promote \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. Obviously, there are many other sectors that are more productive and have greater leverage for growth.\par \par \uc2 Just imagine if the tens of trillions of rupiah already poured into the new capital project were instead used to build a modern \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  transportation system across major cities in the country. The positive impact of such a productive government investment would be immense. It would efficiently improve mobility for the population and certainly spur rapid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth everywhere.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, criticism of the free lunch program leans more towards the huge financial burden that poses risks to the government\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  health. Indeed, the details of the program are not yet clear. However, analysts are now starting to calculate how this program could inflate the government\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If fully implemented, the program would require around Rp450 trillion annually. This could potentially lead to Indonesia falling into a deep \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  trap.\par \par \uc2 Another controversial issue causing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  is the plan to increase the value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) rate, slated to take effect in early 2025. The increase, from 11 percent to 12 percent, is mandated by the Harmonization of \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  Law enacted in 2021.\par \par \uc2 Although Prabowo desires a larger \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue-to-gross domestic product (GDP) ratio, he opposes achieving it through rate hikes. This differing view from an incoming president has thrown this planned increase into limbo. Consequently, the plan to increase the VAT rate is on hold pending the decision of the new government.\par \par \uc2 Unfortunately, this period of political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  coincides with global market turmoil, amidst \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding the possibility of a Federal Reserve interest rate cut. This confluence of negative factors exacerbates the outflow of foreign capital from Indonesia, as investors seek safer havens. Consequently, the rupiah exchange rate is under considerable pressure, and its alleviation seems unlikely until this \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  is resolved.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2024/04/03/858274/858274_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMGEN0020240408ek4300008\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
