\par\par \b \uc2 WB urges new govts to provide  \highlight22\uc2 policy \highlight\uc2  certainty\b0\par\par\uc2 Deni Ghifari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 529 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 April 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The \uc2 World Bank\uc2  urges countries, including Indonesia, to improve \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  clarity for businesses as a sustainable way to push \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, citing the limited \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary room that many countries were facing amid prolonged global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 World Bank East Asia and Pacific vice president \uc2 Manuela Ferro\uc2  said solving \b \highlight22\uc2 policy uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  was critical given that this year many countries would see a change in leadership. The sooner new administrations send their \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  directions to households and companies, the better, she said.\par \par \uc2 "At the end of the day, we are at a time when there's only so much \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  or monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  [we can do to] carry growth in these economies over the long run," Ferro said during an online event on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 "This is a time when businesses would like clarity about the investment regime that they will be operating under. So this is very critical," she added, pointing out that competition-enhancing policies would help attract more investors into \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity.\par \par \uc2 More than half of the world's population will cast their ballot this year. The Asian region has seen nine elections, including Indonesia in February.\par \par \uc2 On March 20, Indonesia's \uc2 General Elections Commission (KPU)\uc2  announced Defense Minister \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  as the winner of the polls, slated to be sworn in this October, alongside his running mate Gibran Rakabuming Raka, incumbent President \uc2 Joko "Jokowi" Widodo\uc2 's eldest son.\par \par \uc2 The \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2  warned in a report in October last year that countries needed to mitigate heightening \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  risks, such as tight financing conditions and mounting concerns for debt vulnerabilities.\par \par \uc2 Speaking at the same event, former finance minister Chatib Basri said macroeconomic stability was one of the key reasons behind Indonesia's ability to maintain relatively strong \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 He pointed out that consumption remained Indonesia's main \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth motor, not investment, with the former contributing over 50 percent of the country's GDP. Hence, the country saw the importance of maintaining inflation.\par \par \uc2 Both monetary and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  authorities in Indonesia have played active roles in pushing down inflation--the former through \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates, while the latter through \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and market interventions.\par \par \uc2 However, the stability, he reasoned, which was paved by both the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies, also provided good grounds for investments coming into Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 World Bank\uc2 's Ferro highlighted that global trade has started to recover after seeing limited improvements last year. The lender projected 2.3 percent growth in external global trade, which would benefit the region, given its ample export activity.\par \par \uc2 However, she noted that the world was facing a negative trend in the sector, calling it a "wave of protectionism" that restricted access to markets.\par \par \uc2 "In 2023 alone, 3,000 new trade-distorting measures were introduced. This is very significant, and it is three times the number of such measures introduced in 2019," said Ferro.\par \par \uc2 Another factor that challenges the trade recovery, said Ferro, was high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the region's major trading partners, namely the \uc2 European Union\uc2  and the United States. Its assessment of inflation data suggests the likeliness of higher \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  for longer, said Ferro.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240404ek450000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
