\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIAN INTEREST MUST BE CONSIDERED IN ROHINGYA REFUGEE ISSUE: GOVT\b0\par\par\uc2 410 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 April 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Rahmad Nasution\par \par \uc2 Banda Aceh, Aceh (ANTARA) - The Aceh Office of Indonesia"s Law and Human Rights Ministry stressed that the handling of Rohingya refugees in Aceh must take into account the country"s national interest.\par \par \uc2 Head of the ministry-Aceh Office, Meurah Budiman, made the statement while receiving a courtesy call of Ann Maymann, a representative at the \uc2 UN Refugee Agency\uc2  (UNHCR Indonesia), here, Thursday.\par \par \uc2 He said the Rohingya refugee crisis is obviously a humanitarian issue but its handling needs to take into account Indonesia"s national interest.\par \par \uc2 During her visit, Maymann discussed with Budiman about issues of the Rohingya refugees being accommodated at several temporary shelters in Aceh.\par \par \uc2 Budiman emphasized that Indonesia has no binding obligation to shelter the Rohingya, as its status is a non-party to the 1951 Convention and its 1967 Protocol.\par \par \uc2 The country"s Constitution, however, upholds the values of humanity, so that the Rohingya refugees are sheltered temporarily, he remarked.\par \par \uc2 He further explained that the handling of foreign refugees in Indonesia has been regulated in Presidential \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  No.125 of 2016.\par \par \uc2 The presidential \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  explicitly necessitates coordination with regional governments in transporting and placing the foreign refugees from where they are found to temporary shelters, Budiman stated.\par \par \uc2 He remarked that the influx of Rohingya refugees into Indonesia, especially Aceh, continued while several locals refused their presence for social and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reasons.\par \par \uc2 Hence, he suggested that related parties need to find a permanent solution to the handling of the Rohingya issue.\par \par \uc2 ANTARA had earlier reported on the local opposition to sheltering Rohingya refugees at a designated campsite in December 2023.\par \par \uc2 As a result, the refugees could not be sheltered at the campsite and were instead sent back to the Aceh Governor"s office.\par \par \uc2 Regarding the Rohingya issue, Foreign Minister \uc2 Retno Marsudi\uc2  has called for a political solution to the matter, which is considered an inseparable part of resolving the Myanmar crisis.\par \par \uc2 During a meeting on the Rohingya issue on the sidelines of the 78th session of the \uc2 UN General Assembly\uc2  in New York, the United States, Marsudi underlined that the future of Rohingya refugees remains \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 At the same time, the global situation and conditions in Myanmar have made the issue more difficult to resolve.\par \par \uc2 "Resolving the Rohingya issue should be part of resolving the political crisis in Myanmar," she remarked.\par \par \uc2 (T.R013/A/T008/T008) 05-04-2024 13:22:09\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240405ek450008d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
