\par\par \b \uc2 Charting out the rupiah exchange rate movement\b0\par\par\uc2 869 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 April 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Fithra Faisal Hastiadi, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The recent fluctuations of the rupiah against the US dollar can be likened to an intricate opera, reminiscent of Richard Wagner's renowned that blend poetry, visual art, music and melancholic drama into a beautiful symphony.\par \par \uc2 Just as Wagner revolutionized opera with his genius for integrating diverse elements, Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  strategy, specifically in its handling of the currency, requires a similarly harmonious approach.\par \par \uc2 The rupiah's decline, influenced by both external and internal pressures, mirrors the complex movements of an orchestral piece. On the external front, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding the \uc2 United States Federal Reserve\uc2 's interest rate policies and robust US data--i.e., US consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the manufacturing purchasing managers' index (PMI)--are contributing to a strengthening US dollar, further exerting pressure on the rupiah. Not to mention, the market still has concerns over Indonesia's over-expansive \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies in \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year 2025.\par \par \uc2 Seasonal trends also play a role, including increased demand for dollars leading up to the Idul Fitri celebrations, foreign profit-taking activities as indicated in broker data, the anticipation of significant US announcements during Indonesian holidays and the approaching period of dividend distributions.\par \par \uc2 Fortunately, the recent statement by Fed chair \uc2 Jerome Powell\uc2 , combined with easing US PMI service data, has helped alleviate tensions in the rupiah. We believe \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  still has room to conduct triple interventions in the market without raising the Seven-Day Reverse Repo Rate in the second quarter. Our impulse response function (IRF) suggests that intervention through foreign exchange (forex) \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  will provide a prompt response to the rupiah's appreciation against the US dollar.\par \par \uc2 The US$142 billion (should be 140) of forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  is still enough to provide that buffer while at the same time collecting all the export proceeds from some of the big exporters that are still not complying with regulations. Our estimates suggest that BI can collect approximately $8 billion to $10 billion of \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  from these exporters, which is more than enough to secure solid forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 A $1 billion intervention will be sufficient to temporarily adjust the rupiah to approximately 15,700 against the US dollar. If this is too expensive, $500 million will suffice to maintain the rupiah at around 15,800.\par \par \uc2 What about the alternative of raising the rate? Our IRF also suggests that increasing it by 25 basis points will, surprisingly, result in a 50-basis point depreciation of the rupiah against the US dollar. However, considering what the \uc2 Bank of Japan\uc2  (BoJ) has done before, raising the rate but observing the yen's depreciation, this is not entirely surprising. Of course, the seven-day rate will eventually cause the rupiah to appreciate in the following months.\par \par \uc2 However, we must be aware that the short-term depreciation will be enough to create an untamed effect of depreciation, further pushing the rupiah to its psychological level of 16,000 against the US. dollar. Additionally, there is a need to be cognizant of the contractionary growth effect it will create in the midterm, costing us \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth momentum and making it harder to achieve 5 percent growth rate this year. Simply put, the interest parity conditions between the BI rate and the Fed rate do not really hold in the short run.\par \par \uc2 In the worst-case scenario, if the pressure against the rupiah continues to persist, the BI can stretch $12 billion of the forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the course of the year to maintain the rupiah at the level of 15,700. The $142 billion of \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  is still enough to provide that buffer while at the same time collecting all the export proceeds from any of the big exporters that are still not complying with regulations.\par \par \uc2 Our estimates suggest that BI can collect approximately $8 billion to $10 billion of \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  from these exporters, which is more than enough to secure solid forex \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In the long term, Indonesia needs a crescendo in export performance, achieved through sustained industrialization. This is the very foundation that will ultimately stabilize the rupiah in the future, given the external pressures. This strategy, however, requires patience and measured steps. Industrial push, like a Wagnerian opera, grows from a deliberate and well-orchestrated process.\par \par \uc2 The rupiah's fluctuations are more than mere numbers; they are a reflection of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  heartbeat. By strategically leveraging interventions, we can ensure that the rupiah not only stabilizes in the short term but also becomes a symbol of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  resilience. The focus should be on turning the rupiah's narrative from one of vulnerability to a tale of triumph, much like the powerful crescendos in Wagner's operas.\par \par \uc2 In conclusion, just as Wagner's operas culminate in a powerful and memorable finale, Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  strategy must aim for a resounding climax that stabilizes and empowers the rupiah. It is a challenging composition, no doubt, but with the right blend of policies and reforms, Indonesia can transform the rupiah's tale into an epic narrative of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  mastery and success.\par \par \uc2 ____________________\par \par \uc2 A senior economist at Samuel Sekuritas Indonesia and a faculty member of University of Indonesia's School of Economics and Business. The views expressed are personal.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240407ek480000e\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw177\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2655\pichgoal600
