\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 RI PROTECTING INVESTMENT CLIMATE FROM IRAN-ISRAEL CONFLICT IMPACTS\b0\par\par\uc2 370 \uc2 words\par \uc2 17 April 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesia is striving to continue \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  restructuring to protect the investment climate from impacts of the boiling geopolitical tensions caused by the Iran-Israel conflict, Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2  stated.\par \par \uc2 "Of course, we need to ensure that the inflow of investment is uninterrupted. To that end, we must genuinely continue \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  restructuring," he remarked in Jakarta on Tuesday (April 16).\par \par \uc2 Hartarto explained that restructuring can be conducted by implementing the Job Creation Law, promoting the development of special \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  zones, completing national strategic projects, and simplifying investment permits.\par \par \uc2 The minister then cited gold and nickel as commodities potentially being targeted by investors in the midst of the souring relations between Iran and Israel.\par \par \uc2 The minister considers gold to be a safe haven of investment, as its prices have been stable amid increasingly \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global conditions. Meanwhile, the price of nickel has increased to US$18 thousand per ton.\par \par \uc2 Hartarto further remarked that an unscathed investment climate and well-running \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  restructuring are expected to help the country survive global and domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  challenges while maintaining national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and completing the development of national strategic projects this year.\par \par \uc2 "To that end, we need to invest even greater efforts since the world is not in a good state," he affirmed.\par \par \uc2 Earlier, on Monday (April 15), Hartarto ensured that the government had prepared several strategic policies to protect Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from the Iran-Israel conflict.\par \par \uc2 "We must maintain the level of market confidence in the ability of the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to respond to conflict escalation impacts," he stated in Jakarta.\par \par \uc2 He also held a meeting with the ambassadors of several friendly countries on the same day to formulate anticipatory measures and plans for coordinating the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  mix with relevant authorities for exchange rate control strategies and \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  management.\par \par \uc2 Israel"s attack on the Consulate of Iran in Damascus, Syria, on April 1, has led to rising tensions between the two countries.\par \par \uc2 In response, Iran retaliated by launching hundreds of ballistic missiles and drones towards Israel on Saturday (April 13).\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-TEG/A/R013/R013) 17-04-2024 12:30:03\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240417ek4h00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
