\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 GOVT REGULARLY DEVISES SCENARIOS TO REDUCE GLOBAL TURMOIL IMPACT\b0\par\par\uc2 354 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 April 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Raka Adji Putra\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs, \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2 , has emphasized that the government regularly prepares scenarios to reduce the impact of global geopolitical turmoil on Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially the real sector.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe government always prepares a scenario. However, now, we are still waiting for developments (in the Iran-Israel conflict)," he informed at a press conference in Jakarta on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 He noted that the potential for escalation of the Iran-Israel conflict is not yet significantly visible. The government is also monitoring the developments between the two countries for potential geopolitical ramifications.\par \par \uc2 Hartarto noted that the statements issued by world leaders have so far tended to be the same, namely wanting to avoid escalation.\par \par \uc2 He further said that neighboring countries around Israel, such as Jordan, Egypt, and Saudi Arabia, have also emphasized the importance of exercising restraint or de-escalation.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe \uc2 UN\uc2  Secretary-General has also asked all parties to exercise restraint and is seeking to control the escalation in the situation. Earlier, Iran also stated that it is still awaiting a statement from the \uc2 UN\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D he remarked.\par \par \uc2 The minister noted that investors have a good level of confidence in the resilience of Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also estimated to continue growing at around 5 percent this year.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIndonesia is far above the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development (which is predicted to grow 3.2 percent in 2024). The global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is projected to flatten while Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s (\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth) is projected to be at 5.1 percent in 2025,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 According to him, Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  resilience is evident from surveys by several rating agencies, including \uc2 Moody\u8217\'20\'19s\uc2 , which released its report on April 16, 2024.\par \par \uc2 In its report, \uc2 Moody\u8217\'20\'19s\uc2  maintained Indonesia"s sovereign credit rating (SCR) at Baa2, one level above investment grade, with a stable outlook.\par \par \uc2 It assessed that Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  resilience is maintained with high and stable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and several strong \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  instruments amid global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-RAP/B/A063/A063) 18-04-2024 23:11:27\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240418ek4i001b9\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b \uc2 Kadin's \uc2 Anindya Bakrie\uc2  Addresses Geopolitical Concerns at ICC Paris\b0\par\par\uc2 623 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 April 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Paris. Chairman of the Advisory Board at the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) \uc2 Anindya Novyan Bakrie\uc2  asserts that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals are robust enough to withstand the impact of global geopolitical and geoeconomic factors, including the Middle East crisis.\par \par \uc2 "Indonesia's \b \high