\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIA EXPERIENCED IN MANAGING INFLATION AMID GLOBAL TENSIONS: GOVT\b0\par\par\uc2 359 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 April 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesia has been learning from its experiences in dealing with the inflation rate in the midst of global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as during rising tensions between Russia and Ukraine, Coordinating \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Minister \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2  affirmed.\par \par \uc2 "We have gained experiences from how we dealt with inflation during the Ukrainian conflict, as evidenced by our success in controlling our inflation rate," he remarked at a press conference in Jakarta on Thursday (April 18).\par \par \uc2 Hartarto made the statement amid concerns over conflicts in the Middle East, including the one involving Iran and Israel, affecting Indonesia"s inflation rate.\par \par \uc2 The minister noted that the raging conflict between Russia and Ukraine had increased Indonesia"s inflation rate to 5.95 percent. However, the government has managed to tame the rate, pegging it at around 2.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 Hartarto stated that the national inflation rate has been mostly affected by food commodities while attributing their spiking prices to the global heat phenomenon El Nino from July 2023 until March this year.\par \par \uc2 "Hence, our inflation rate does not depend on conflicts in the Middle East. The rate has been mostly affected by domestic factors and the El Nino," he underscored.\par \par \uc2 The minister further remarked that the prices of several food commodities, such as rice, cooking oil, and chilies, had started to return to the normal level and had even declined.\par \par \uc2 Hartarto affirmed that the government has been intensively coordinating with central and regional inflation controlling teams to ensure that the inflation rate remains at around 2.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 The central and regional governments have also been stepping up coordination with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to protect the national inflation rate from the impacts of global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he added.\par \par \uc2 According to the minister, Indonesia has been making use of monetary policies, pro-stability and pro-growth policies, and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies to control its inflation rate.\par \par \uc2 He also noted that the government had devised four strategies to control inflation, namely pursuing affordable prices, sufficient stocks, well-running distribution processes, as well as effective communication.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-TEG/B/A043/A043) 19-04-2024 14:52:25\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240419ek4j0008d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
