\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  GROWTH IN 2024 Q1, Q2 PROJECTED SURPASSING Q4 OF 2023\b0\par\par\uc2 360 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 April 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Raka Adji Putra\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  forecast Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the 2024 first (Q1) and second (Q2) quarters to be higher than in the 2023 fourth quarter (Q4), with support from strong domestic demand.\par \par \uc2 "\b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the first and second quarters of 2024 is predicted to be higher than the fourth quarter of 2023, supported by domestic demand that remains strong from household consumption in line with Ramadan and Eid al-Fitr," he stated here on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 He made the statement at a virtual press conference on the results of the meeting of the BI Board of Governors for April 2024.\par \par \uc2 According to data from Statistics Indonesia (BPS), Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth was recorded at 5.04 percent year-on-year in Q4 of 2023.\par \par \uc2 Warjiyo noted that Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  remained resilient amid increasing global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Building investment was higher than forecast, supported by the continuation of National Strategic Projects (PSN) in several regions and the development of private properties as a positive impact of government incentives.\par \par \uc2 However, he emphasized that household consumption and non-building investment should continue to be pushed to support the continuity of national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the performance of goods" exports is not yet strong, influenced by the decline in commodity exports in line with falling commodity prices and demand from main trading partners, such as China, which is still weak.\par \par \uc2 In terms of the business fields, the processing industry, information and communications, wholesale and retail trade, and construction sectors are predicted to grow strongly.\par \par \uc2 Spatially, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in all regions remains good, supported by domestic demand, especially household consumption.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2024 is projected to lie in the range of 4.7 percent to 5.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 BI has stated that going forward, it will continue to bolster the synergy of policies with the government, including through government \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  and BI"s macroprudential \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 , to support sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, especially in terms of domestic demand.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-RAP/B/A063/A063) 24-04-2024 18:39:26\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240424ek4o00105\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b \uc2 BI Raises  \highlight22\uc2 Interest Rates \highlight\uc2  to 6.25 Percent Over Geopolitical Concerns\b0\par\par\uc2 814 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 April 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  increased the benchmark BI-Rate by 25 basis points to 6.25 percent, citing escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East and rising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the US, causing the rupiah to weaken.\par \par \uc2 During its Board of Governors Meeting on April 23-24, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  also raised the Deposit Facility rate to 5.5 percent and the Lending Facility rate to 7 percent.\par \par \uc2 "This rate hike aims to strengthen the rupiah exchange rate amid worsening global risks and to ensure inflation remains within the target of 2.5 plus-minus 1 percent in 2024. It is in line with our pro-stability \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  stance," said BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  during a press conference after the monthly Board of Governors Meeting on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 This is the first interest rate hike since October 2023 and was contrary to analysts' expectations.\par \par \uc2 Perry said that global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial dynamics were rapidly changing due to increasing risks and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  stemming from changes in US monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East.\par \par \uc2 "As a result, global investors are shifting their portfolios to safer assets, particularly the US dollar and gold, leading to capital outflows and further depreciation of currencies in emerging markets," explained Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 According to Perry, high inflation and robust \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the United States were fueling speculation of a smaller and longer-than-expected decline in the \uc2 US Federal Reserve\uc2 's benchmark interest rate (Fed Funds Rate/FFR), in line with statements from \uc2 Federal Reserve\uc2  officials. This, along with the US's increasing debt needs, has led to a continuous increase in \uc2 US Treasury\uc2  yields and a stronger US dollar globally.\par \par \uc2 "The strengthening of the US dollar is also driven by the weakening of several world currencies such as the Japanese Yen and the Chinese Yuan," added Perry.\par \par \uc2 Moving forward, risks related to the direction of the FFR decline and global geopolitical tensions will continue to be monitored as they could lead to further \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in global financial markets, increased inflationary pressures, and decreased prospects for global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 "These conditions require a strong \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  response to mitigate the negative impact of global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the economies of developing countries, including Indonesia," said Perry.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is considered resilient amidst increasing global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the first and second quarters of 2024 is expected to be higher than in the fourth quarter of 2023, supported by strong domestic demand from household consumption in line with the seasonal Eid trend.\par \par \uc2 Investment in construction is higher than expected, supported by the continuation of National Strategic Projects (PSN) in several regions and the growth of private property due to government incentives. With these developments, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in 2024 is estimated to be in the range of 4.7-5.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 "In the future, BI will continue to strengthen \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  synergy with the Government, including through the Government's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's macroprudential \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2 , to support sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, especially from the domestic demand side," added Perry.\par \par \uc2 The rate hike was contrary to analysts' expectations, who anticipated BI to maintain its benchmark interest rate.\par \par \uc2 Teuku Riefky, an economist from the Institute for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Social Research (LPEM) Faculty of Economics and Business, University of Indonesia (FEB UI), had recommended \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  to maintain its benchmark interest rate at 6 percent to mitigate the impact of geopolitical tensions in the Middle East.\par \par \uc2 "The rupiah is currently facing significant currency pressure and a surge in capital outflows over the past two weeks, triggered by geopolitical tensions in the Middle East," said Teuku Riefky in Jakarta on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 So far, the rupiah has depreciated by around 2.98 percent month-to-month or 5.5 percent year-to-date against the US dollar and is one of the worst-performing currencies compared to peer countries, only performing better than the Brazilian real in the last month.\par \par \uc2 "Although there is room for a benchmark interest rate hike, the decision to raise BI's benchmark interest rate does not seem to be the ideal step to take at this time," he added.\par \par \uc2 Head Economist of Bank Permata, Josua Pardede, said that if the BI-Rate is raised, the positive impact would be that the pressure from external factors could ease because there is an expansion of the positive spread with the yield of financial instruments from other countries, making Indonesian financial instruments more attractive due to compensation for the increase in risk premiums.\par \par \uc2 The negative impact is that the burden of yields on domestic financial instruments will increase and become a burden for instrument enthusiasts.\par \par \uc2 "In addition, the increase in the BI-Rate can lead to an increase in lending rates, thus increasing borrowing costs, ultimately potentially hindering Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth potential," added Josua.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020240424ek4o00006\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw177\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\pi