\par\par \b \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  Says BI Rate Hike Important Amidst Global  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainties \highlight\uc2 , Fluctuations\b0\par\par\uc2 386 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 April 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - State-owned \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  (IDX: BMRI) reacted well to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's (BI) decision to raise its benchmark interest rate. In its board meeting today, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  decided to raise the benchmark interest rate to 6.25 percent in a bid to boost the rupiah's stability.\par \par \uc2 "We believe that maintaining financial stability is very important for the financial sector, especially the banking sector, and the macroeconomy," \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 's corporate secretary Teuku Ali Usman said in a written statement on Wednesday, April 24.\par \par \uc2 He said that the rate hike will allow the banking sector to implement better and more prudent strategies amidst various global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and fluctuations.\par \par \uc2 According to \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of raising the BI 7-day Reverse Repo Rate (BI7DRR) is a pre-emptive and anticipatory measure by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The aim is to ensure that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial markets remain stable amid escalating global risks.\par \par \uc2 "These include the geopolitical conflict in the Middle East and the potential for a possible delay in the reduction of the US interest rate or Fed Funds Rate (FFR)," Teuku said.\par \par \uc2 The BI's Board of Governors meeting on April 23-24 decided to raise the BI rate by 25 basis points to 6.25 percent. The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  raised the deposit facility rate to 5.50 percent. Meanwhile, the lending facility rate was raised by 7 percent.\par \par \uc2 BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  said the increase was aimed at strengthening the stability of the rupiah exchange rate against the possibility of worsening global risks. It is also a preemptive and forward-looking measure to ensure that inflation remains within the target range of 2.5 percent, \u177\'00\'B11, for this year and 2025, which is in line with the pro-stability monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In terms of macroprudential policies and payment systems, Perry said the BI remains pro-growth to support sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. Perry said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  continues to pursue macroprudential policies to encourage banks to lend and finance both businesses and households.\par \par \uc2 RIANI SANUSI PUTRI | ANNISA FEBIOLA\par \par \uc2 Editor's Choice: \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Raises Key Interest Rate to 6.25% to Bolster Rupiah Stability\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2024/03/05/id_1284950/1284950_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240425ek4p00002\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b \uc2 BI's Rate Hike Sinks IDX, Investors Worry About Credit Slowdown\b0\par\par\uc2 491 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 April 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. The \uc2 Indonesia Stock Exchange\uc2  (IDX) saw a drop in the Composite Stock Price Index at the opening of Thursday's trading session, falling to 7,176 and briefly touching a low of 7,132. This drop followed \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's (BI) decision to raise the benchmark interest rate (BI rate) to 6.25 percent on Wednesday. The increase was met with negative responses from market participants due to several concerns.\par \par \uc2 According to Reza Priyambada, an Investment Consultant at Reliance Sekuritas, the hike in the BI rate raised concerns about a potential slowdown in bank credit disbursement. Businesses are also reevaluating decisions to take loans with high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  looms regarding the direction of the \uc2 Federal Reserve\uc2 's (The Fed) Fed Funds Rate (FFR) cuts this year.\par \par \uc2 "There is no firm statement from The Fed indicating that the FFR will decrease in a certain month. This has led the market to reconsider whether domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  will rise while the global FFR level remains unclear," Reza Priyambada told Investor Daily TV (IDTV) on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 He said that if the credit \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  for retail or small enterprises shift to around 9-10 percent, and for corporates, it may vary between 12% or maybe 14-15%, there is still a significant spread, even though the BI rate is 6.25 percent.\par \par \uc2 "We hope there will be no adjustment in credit \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to cushion the impact," he said.\par \par \uc2 Reza added that the increase in credit \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  could also pose challenges for creditors due to increased costs. Therefore, such adjustments should not occur, especially considering that the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is still in the recovery phase post-Covid-19 pandemic.\par \par \uc2 "We shouldn't face such conditions at a time like this," he emphasized.\par \par \uc2 According to senior economist and Associate Faculty at the Indonesian Banking Development Institute, Ryan Kiryanto, the BI-rate increase can still be tolerated by market participants and businesses.\par \par \uc2 "Although the 25 bps increase is considered non-aggressive, banks and financing institutions need to recalculate their operations," said Ryan.\par \par \uc2 Ryan emphasized the importance of banks maintaining a balance between the interests of creditors and debtors to avoid disrupting \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities.\par \par \uc2 "Stress tests need to be conducted to test the resilience of banks against increasing risks, both in global geopolitics and current monetary policies," he added.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Bank Danamon economist, Irman Faiz, said that BI's move showed its readiness to face pressure on the rupiah.\par \par \uc2 "BI seems to be preparing to mitigate pressure on the rupiah by raising the money market interest rate and responding to the increase in yields," said Irman.\par \par \uc2 Irman also predicted that BI would remain proactive in implementing interest rate hikes if pressure on the rupiah continues.\par \par \uc2 "We predict that BI will not lower the benchmark interest rate in 2024, considering the high benchmark interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  applied by the Fed," said Irman.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020240425ek4p0000a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
