\par\par \b \uc2 BI Rate rise increases stability while maintaining growth\b0\par\par\uc2 861 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 May 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Ardhienus , Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) Board of Governors Meeting on April 23-24 decided to raise the benchmark interest rate (BI Rate) by 25 basis points to 6.25 percent, breaking through the 6 percent rate that had been maintained for six months since October 2023 to reach the highest level since April 2015.\par \par \uc2 Raising the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark interest rate was not a popular decision, but the monetary measure was an appropriate action for two reasons.\par \par \uc2 First, it was made in response to a global turmoil that has turned out to be increasingly \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , from the \uc2 United States Federal Reserve\uc2 's delay in accelerating the reduction of its benchmark interest rate in line with US inflation, which is still above the targeted 2 percent (higher for longer), and to geopolitical factors such as Russia's unending war on Ukraine, which has been exacerbated by the escalation of war between Israel and Gaza in the Middle East to involve Iran.\par \par \uc2 As is always the case, emergence of global turmoil will move funds from emerging countries to safe haven assets, especially US dollars (flight to quality).\par \par \uc2 Big and institutional portfolio investors are worried about their funds. As a result, the US dollar exchange rate has predictably strengthened against many other countries' currencies, including the rupiah, which even exceeded Rp 16,000 per US dollar last week.\par \par \uc2 The second reason is to anchor future inflation within BI's corridor of 2.5 plus/minus 1 percent in 2024 and 2025. There appears to be stronger inflationary pressure in the future, especially from food inflation, which will cause inflation to continue rising this year.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to raise the benchmark interest rate shows that BI remains consistent with its pro-stability \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in navigating the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Various responses have certainly arisen from those who agree and disagree with this measure. It is indeed a dilemmatic decision. On the one hand, it will stabilize the rupiah's value against both the US dollar (exchange rate) and goods and services (inflation), but on the other hand, a higher benchmark interest rate will boost the cost of funds so loan \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be higher. In the end, loan disbursement will falter and threaten \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 However, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  included this unpleasant effect in its calculations when issuing its latest decision to increase the BI Rate. The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  did not deny the impact, so it therefore also provided a sweet jamu (herbal medicine) in the form of macroprudential liquidity incentives to the banking industry.\par \par \uc2 These are all part of the BI \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  mix that has been a mainstay so far,\par \par \uc2 The Macroprudential Liquidity \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  (KLM), which provides incentives in the form of eased reserve requirements (GWM) by a maximum of 4 percent, was issued in October 2023.\par \par \uc2 The banking industry has since enjoyed an abundance of liquidity from BI, which is why the additional liquidity encouraged credit growth to 12.40 percent up to March 2024.\par \par \uc2 However, in observing the various current conditions, BI has expanded the scope of priority sectors that can obtain the liquidity incentives, such as supporting downstream sectors, construction and productive real estate, the creative \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and automotive. These sectors are deemed to leverage the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . In addition to expanding the scope of sectors, BI has also adjusted the amount of incentives for each sector.\par \par \uc2 According to BI data, the macroprudential liquidity incentives have reached Rp 165 trillion (US$10.3 billion) as of March 2024. If the expanded category of sectors is utilized properly, total KLM disbursements of could exceed Rp 280 trillion by December 2024.\par \par \uc2 The additional liquidity will stimulate credit growth in line with The BI target of 10-12 percent this year and as such, minimize the feared negative impact of a higher BI Rate on credit growth that could lead to a slowdown in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . With credit growth within the target range, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will also remain within the range of 4.7 to 5.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 Banks are also not expected to experience significant liquidity difficulties or tightening, because the liquidity incentive can serve as ammunition to disburse loans.\par \par \uc2 In addition, banks also have quite abundant liquidity at present. This can be seen from the high ratio of liquid assets to third-party funds reaching 27.18 percent in the first quarter of 2024. This means that banks do not need to fight for \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds by raising deposit rates. With such a scenario, the cost of funds will remain under control and lending rates will remain stable, or at least will increase slightly so as not to burden debtors.\par \par \uc2 Banks' intermediation activities will continue to provide increased net interest income while maintaining credit quality. Liquidity conditions will also remain at safe levels.\par \par \uc2 However, the effectiveness of BI's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  mix still requires \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  support and coordination, especially from the government. In this case, the government can also provide \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives and other supporting policies. Thus, while strengthening monetary stability, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will still reach the target.\par \par \uc2 ____________________\par \par \uc2 The deputy director of macroprudential, monetary and market surveillance at \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The views expressed are personal.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240505ek560000h\par }\par \b \uc2 Search Summary\b0\par \par  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx2000\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx9072\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Text\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \li50\uc2 (economic or economy) and (uncertain or uncertainty or uncertainties) and (policy or public or tax or taxation or taxes or taxed or spending or expenditure or fiscal or stimulus or budget or deficit or national debt or tariff or subsidies or subsidy or Bank Indonesia or central bank or reserves or interest rates or fiscal or legislation or legislative or house of representatives or regulation)\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx2000\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx9072\row } \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx2000\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx9072\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlp